<TITLE>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - Macintosh</TITLE>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_155.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_157.html">next</A> section.<P>
<H3><A NAME="SEC159" HREF="bdg_toc.html#SEC159">Macintosh</A></H3>
<B>sumex-aim.stanford.edu</B>
This is the premier site for Macintosh
software.  After you log in, switch to the info-mac directory, which will
bring up a long series of sub-directories of virtually every free and
shareware Mac program you could ever want.
<A NAME="IDX388"></A>
9 p.m. - 9 a.m.
<P>
<B>ftp.uu.net</B>
You'll find lots of Macintosh programs in the 
<TT>`systems/mac/simtel20'</TT> directory. 
Available 24 hours a day.
<P>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_155.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_157.html">next</A> section.<P>
