<TITLE>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - More Educational Resources</TITLE>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_247.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_249.html">next</A> section.<P>
<H3><A NAME="SEC251" HREF="bdg_toc.html#SEC251">More Educational Resources</A></H3>
To get a list of ftp sites that carry astronomical images
in the GIF graphics format, use ftp to connect to <B>nic.funet.fi</B>. Switch
to the <TT>`/pub/astro/general'</TT> directory and get the file <TT>`astroftp.txt'</TT>.
Among the sites listed is <B>ames.arc.nasa.gov</B>, which carries images
taken by the Voyager and Galileo probes, among other pictures.
<P>
