<TITLE>Big Dummy's Guide to the Internet - Main nameservers</TITLE>
<P>Go to the <A HREF="bdg_285.html">previous</A>, <A HREF="bdg_287.html">next</A> section.<P>
<H2><A NAME="SEC289" HREF="bdg_toc.html#SEC289">Main nameservers</A></H2>
<P>
This is the main nameserver as listed in the <B>rs.internic.net</B>
database.
Those often change as the network grows, and it is hard to keep track of
all nameservers, but they should usually work. Nameservers can be
queried by users using <SAMP>`nslookup'</SAMP>.
<P>
