<H1>Satellite Images and Data Sets</H1>
<HR>

There is a separate page for <a href="invdir.html">Inventory and Directory Services</a>.
<p>
For a load of pointers to images check out the <A HREF="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/weather/top.html"><b>Weather FAQ</b></a>!
<p>
<a href="gcservers.html">Environmental and Global Change Infoservers</a>
<p>
<A HREF="http://global.esrin.esa.it:8000/~nick/satfaq.html">Satellite Imagery Proto-FAQ</A>
<br>
<a href="http://www.geog.nottingham.ac.uk/remote/satfaq.html">UK mirror of the SATFAQ</a>
<br>
<a href="http://giant.mindlink.net/geo_exchange/satfaq.html">Another SATFAQ site</a>
<br>
<a href="http://www.uni-sb.de/philfak/fb6/fr66/tpw/rem_sens/satfaq.html">SATFAQ site in Germany</a>
<br>
The plain text version should now be available on news.answers,
and by anonymous ftp from rtfm.mit.edu.   The archive name is
sci/Satellite-Imagery-FAQ
<p>
Also check out the InterFAQ on the <a href="http://clever.net/webthing/">WebThing</a>
by <a href="http://clever.net/webthing/people/nick/Nick.html">Nick Kew</a>!
<br>
The WebThing has a <a href="http://clever.net/webthing/RS">Remote Sensing Thing</a> going on.


