<h2>The DAAC's</h2>
Here's an <a href="http://www-nsidc.colorado.edu/NASA/cdrom_data_products.html">Overview of the DAAC's</a>
<ul>
<LI><A HREF="http://wwwdaac.msfc.nasa.gov/">NASA Marshall Space Flight Center DAAC</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://podaac-www.jpl.nasa.gov">PO.DAAC JPL</A>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://podaac.jpl.nasa.gov">PO.DAAC on FTP</A>

<li><a href="http://eosims.asf.alaska.edu:12355/asf_homepage.html"><b>ASF DAAC  </b></a> -Alaska SAR Facility:  
<i>Polar processes, SAR products</i>
<li><a href="http://sun1.cr.usgs.gov/landdaac/landdaac.html"><b>EDC DAAC  </b></a> -EROS Data Center:  <i>Land processes</i>
<li><a href="http://www.ciesin.org/IC/SEDAC/SEDAC-home.html"><b>CIESIN-SEDAC  </b></a> -The Consortium for International Earth Science 
Information Network - Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center:  <i>Human Dimensions of Global Environmental Change</i>
<li><a href="http://daac.gsfc.nasa.gov/DAAC_DOCS/gdaac_home.html"><b>GSFC DAAC  </b></a>-Goddard Space Flight Center:
 <i>Upper atmosphere, global biosphere, atmospheric dynamics, geophysics</i>
<li><a href="http://podaac-www.jpl.nasa.gov/"><b>JPL DAAC </b></a>-Jet Propulsion Lab:  <i>Physical Oceanography</i>
<li><a href="http://eosdis.larc.nasa.gov/"><b>LARC DAAC </b></a>-Langley Research Center:  <i>Radiation budget, tropospheric chemistry, clouds, aerosols</i>
<li><a href="http://wwwdaac.msfc.nasa.gov/"><b>MSFC DAAC </b></a>-Marshall Space Flight Center: <i>Hydrologic cycle</i>
<li><a href="http://www.saa.noaa.gov/"><b>NOAA SAA </b></a>-National Oceanic and Atmospheric
Administration - Satellite Active Archive:  <i>Satellite Data (Atmosphere, Land, Ocean, Earth Sciences, Remote Sensing)</i>
<li><a href="http://eosims.colorado.edu:1733/"><b>NSIDC DAAC </b></a>-National Snow and Ice Data Center:  <i>Snow and ice, cryosphere and climate</i>
<li><a href="http://www-eosdis.ornl.gov/"><b>ORNL DAAC </b></a>-Oak Ridge National Lab:  <i>Biogeochemical dynamics</i>
</ul>
<hr>

