<h2>Receiving Equipment and Software for HRPT/AVHRR</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="suppliers.html">List of suppliers of HRPT receiving equipment</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.satlantic.com/">Satlantic Inc., HRPT/SeaWIFS receiving stations</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.seaspace.com/">SeaSpace</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.seaspace.com/terascan.html">The TeraScan receiving system of SeaSpace</A>
<LI><A HREF="mailto:chips@geogr.ku.dk">CHIPS from the Geographical Institute - Copenhagen, Denmark</a>
<br>
CHIPS is a shareware package for AVHRR processing.
<br>
They do have an anonymous FTP site at <a href="ftp://ftp.geogr.ku.dk/">ftp.geogr.ku.dk</a>, but it doesn't seem
to work with my web browser. Check out the directories pub/chips (for the DOS
version) and pub/chips/winchips (for the prerelease Windows version).
<li><a href="http://stratus.bu.edu/caspr/caspr.html">The Cloud and Surface Parameter Retrieval (CASPR) System for Polar AVHRR (runs on IDL)</a>
<li><a href="http://smis.iki.rssi.ru/scanor_main.html">The SCANOR system, Space Monitoring Information Support laboratory, Space Research Institute, Russia</a>
<li><a href="http://kurgan.colorado.edu/personnel/professionals/baldwin/baldwin_root.html">Dan Baldwin, the main contact for distribution of public domain
satellite navigation software</a>
<li><a href="http://kurgan.colorado.edu/personnel/professors/emery/emery_root.html">Professor William J. Emery</a>
<li><a href="ftp://loaser.univ-lille1.fr/SPHINX/">SPHINX, Image Processing using Orbital Models</a>, version 3.8
<li><a href="las.html">LAS & XID & ADAPS</a> from <a href="http://edcwww.cr.usgs.gov/">EROS Data Center</a>
<pre>
<b>LAS</b>   - Land Analysis System
<b>XID</b>   - X Image Display program
<b>ADAPS</b> - AVHRR Data Acquisition and Processing System
</pre>
LAS seems to be available for SGI (IRIX 4.0.5, IRIX 5.1.1.3), Data General (DG/UX 5.4.1+2), Sun (SunOS 4.1.3)
<li><a href="http://daac.gsfc.nasa.gov/CAMPAIGN_DOCS/OCDST/OB_SEAPAK.html">SEAPAK for CZCS and AVHRR processing and interpretation</a>
<li><a href="ftp://ftp.sat.dundee.ac.uk/programs/">Programs for reading and converting the Dundee HRPT format</a>
<li>The low-cost <a href="http://http://www.msoft.it/noaa95/">NOAA95 HRPT receiver kit</a>.
</ul>

<h2>Data Providers</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://atlas.esrin.esa.it:8000/">The (Un)Official Global 1KM AVHRR Server!</a>
