<H1>Useful Internet "Things"</H1>
<H2>Webs</H2>
<UL>
<li><a href="http://www.w3.org/"><b>Home of the Web!</b></a><img src="logo/web.xbm" alt="" align=top>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.tu-graz.ac.at/">Hyper-G W3 Entry Point</A>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.esrin.esa.it/pub/Hyper-G">Hyper-G mirror at Esrin</A>
</UL>

<h2>Internet Guides</h2>
<ul>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hensa.ac.uk/mirror/http://nearnet.gnn.com/wic/newrescat.toc.html">The Whole Internet Catalog</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://slacvx.slac.stanford.edu/misc/internet-services.html">Special Internet Connections, Scott Yanoff</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://nearnet.gnn.com/nav/navforum.html">Welcome New Navigators!</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://nearnet.gnn.com/wic/newrescat.toc.html">The Whole Internet Catalog</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://cs.indiana.edu/docproject/zen/zen-1.0.html">ZEN and the Art of the Internet</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.earn.net/gnrt/notice.html">The Guide to Network Resource Tools</A>
<li><a href="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/WWW/MarkUp/html3/Contents.html">HyperText Markup Language Specification 3.0</a>
<li><a href="http://www.sandia.gov/sci_compute/html_ref.html">HTML Reference Manual</a>
<li><a href="http://hoohoo.ncsa.uiuc.edu/docs/Overview.html">NCSA HTTPd Overview</a>
</ul>

<h2>FAQs</h2>
<ul>
