>From etrheim@sg2.cr.usgs.gov Thu Mar 28 14:27:20 1996
From: etrheim@sg2.cr.usgs.gov (Daniel Etrheim)
Subject: las.discalimer
To: james.c.tilton.1@gsfc.nasa.gov
Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit


                 ********  Disclaimer  ********

The EROS Data Center has provided LAS to outside users for over
12 years and has provided limited support.  The LAS, ADAPS, XID,
and TIEPTS systems have been developed to support research and
development of image processing applications within NASA and the
USGS. Since the software is public-domain, it is available to any
government or private institution.

As the popularity of these systems has grown, so has the impact
of external support on EDC resources.  This impact has greatly
hampered the continued development of EDC's internal image
processing capabilities.  As a result, EDC can no longer provide
external support.  Occasionally, limited support will be considered
for agencies with whom we have cooperative agreements or mutual goals.

All requests for copies of these software packages must be made
formally and should state that you have read and understand this
disclaimer.  Requests should be mailed or faxed to:

                                    Office of the Chief
                                    EROS Data Center
                                    U.S. Geological Survey
                                    Sioux Falls, SD 57198
                                    FAX: 605-594-6154


                       ****************

LAS - The Land Analysis System is an image processing, image analysis
      and raster GIS system developed cooperatively by NASA's
      Goddard Space Flight Center (GSFC) and the U.S. Geological
      Survey's EROS Data Center (EDC).

XID - The X Image Display program allows users to display and
      interactively manipulate images on display terminals running the
      X Window System.  The TIEPTS program allows users to interactively
      select tie points between unregistered images and a reference source,
      such as a registered image, a base map, or vector data. These
      programs were developed at EDC and are distributed with the LAS system.

ADAPS - The AVHRR Data Acquisition and Processing System is a reception,
      processing, and product generation system for AVHRR imagery from
      NOAA satellites.  This system was developed at EDC using the LAS
      system and additional capabilities.

Documentation for these systems (except ADAPS) is provided in Hyper Text
Markup Language (HTML) and PostScript format.

LAS is currently available on the following platforms:
   Silicon Graphics: Built and tested on IRIX 4.0.5,
                     Tested on IRIX 5.1.1.3
   Data General:     Built and tested on DG/UX 5.4.1,
                     Tested on DG/UX 5.4.2
   Sun:              Built and tested on Sun/OS 4.1.3

If you have questions, please contact Dan Etrheim, (605) 594-6860
or INTERNET:etrheim@edcserver1.cr.usgs.gov.


------------------------------
Dan Etrheim
Technical Area Leader
Scientific Systems Development
Hughes/STX
etrheim@sg2.cr.usgs.gov
(605)594-6860
------------------------------
