<head>
<title>Wim Bakker, Curriculum Vitae</title>
</head>
<body>
<pre>
<h2>CURRICULUM VITAE</h2>

NAME              <b>Wim Harry Bakker</b>
ADDRESS           Estrikstraat 12
                  7531 ZR Enschede
                  the Netherlands
TELEPHONE         ++31-53 334229
DATE OF BIRTH     2 January 1960
PLACE OF BIRTH    Leeuwarden (NL)

NATIONALITY       Dutch (NL)
MARRIED TO        Francis F.M. Riesthuis
CHILDREN          2

<h3>EDUCATION</h3>

1978-1985         Study of Electrical Engineering at Twente University.
                  Degree: Btw, Bachelor Technical Sciences
                  (Baccalaureaats Technische Wetenschappen) 

to 1978           Primary and Secondary school at Leeuwarden

<h3>LANGUAGE & DEGREE OF PROFICIENCY</h3>

                  LANGUAGE    SPEAKING   READING     WRITING
                  o Dutch     Native Language
                  o English   Excellent  Excellent   Excellent
                  o German    Good       Good        Moderate
                  o French    Moderate   Fair        Poor

<h3>FIELD OF EXPERTISE</h3>

                  Software development for the UNIX operating system &
                  environment in the "C" and other programming languages.
                  Extensive knowledge of Image Processing & Remote Sensing.
                  Extensive knowledge of the Internet and software tools from/for
                  the Internet.

<h3>EMPLOYMENT RECORD</h3>

<b>1994-</b>             From 20-7-1994 to date
EMPLOYER          The International Institute for Aerospace Survey and Earth
                  Sciences (ITC)
POSITION HELD     Information Engineer
DESCRIPTION OF DUTIES
                  Software development for the UNIX environment and other
                  platforms, in the "C" and other programming language, for the
                  production of satellite images and education in Image Processing
                  and Remote Sensing.
                  Development, teaching and giving practical training within the
                  course "Digital Image Processing" (DIP5/IGP3). Writing lecture
                  notes for this course.
                  Maintaining information on the Internet, especially for the World
                  Wide Web (WWW). Maintenance of various software tools
                  from/for the Internet; new programming languages like Perl and
                  HTML; new WWW tools like the NCSA Web-server and Mosaic and
                  Lynx Web-browsers.
		  Production of Remote Sensing images and data sets for staff,
		  students and third parties.

<b>1993-1994</b>         From 19-7-1993 to 20-7-1994
EMPLOYER          The International Institute for Aerospace Survey and Earth
                  Sciences (ITC)
POSITION HELD     Software Developer & Project Manager
DESCRIPTION OF DUTIES
                  Project manager for the Alexander project funded by the BCRS.
                  Contributed a report: "Remote Sensing Data and GIS Data on
                  CD-ROM".
                  Software development for Alexander concerning a query language
                  for area properties in segmented images.

<b>1990-1993</b>         From 1-10-1990 to 16-7-1993
EMPLOYER          IMIX V.O.F. - Vision Support Systems
POSITION HELD     Technical Manager & Co-owner
DESCRIPTION OF DUTIES
                  Founded a private company, IMIX V.O.F. - Vision Support
                  Systems, together with two partners H.L.M. van Huijstee and P.
                  Kok.
                  Main objective of IMIX is to build low cost image processing
                  solutions (software and hardware) for industry and institutes.

                  Main market of IMIX:

                  o     Production factories:
                        o quality control  o detection
                        o process control  o measurement

                  o     Research institutes:
                        o image analysis   o data reduction
                        o Remote Sensing   o education

                  Relevant experience gathered during the IMIX period:
                  o     Extensive knowledge of the C language, shell scripts and
                        the Unix operating system.
                  o     Programming user interfaces in XWindows.
                  o     Installation and maintenance of many Public Domain (PD)
                        software packages, for example:
                        o     Postgres, a database management system from the
                              University of California. This was used to reach a
                              systematic approach of image processing using the
                              embedded query language of postgres (PostQuel)
                        o     Khoros, the extensive image processing package
                              from the University of New Mexico
                  o     Development and teaching of the course "Computer
                        Vision" at the Hogeschool Utrecht (pyrotechnical school) at
                        the division Industrial Automation and Computer Integrated
                        Manufacturing.
                        Writing of lecture notes for this course.
                  o     Maintenance and programming a Sun SparcStation 1+ with
                        VideoPix frame grabber board.
                  o     Consultancy to the ITC's Image Processing Laboratory
                        (IPL) for the production of satellite images, software
                        development and retrieving and maintenance of software
                        packages.

                        Production is: retrieving data, making subsets, hardcopies,
                        doing early stage processing, filtering, classification etc.

                        Production shifted from the old PDP's to the modern HP
                        workstations, making efficient use of available hardware
                        resources and the network.
                        The Erdas image file format was adapted as the standard
                        image format for programs.

                        Numerous packages were collected from the Internet and
                        adapted for IPL. These programs help to speed up
                        production and increase the capabilities of the IPL.

                        Used Hardware & Software at the ITC:
                        o     HP 9000/720 + HP-UX 9
                        o     Sun SparcStation 2 + SunOS 4.1.3
                        o     Sun3/GOP (special IP hardware) + SunOS 4.1
                        o     PC + MS-DOS 6.2  o     Archimedes + RiscOS
                        o     VAX + VMS        o     PDP11/44 + RSX11
                        o     Erdas 7.5        o     Imagine 8.0
                        o     Ilwis 1.4        o     Idrisi 4.0
                        o     Many PD packages (Khoros, xv, pbmplus, tiff, jpeg
                              etc. etc.)

<b>1985-1990</b>         From 1-10-85 to 31-9-90
EMPLOYER          University of Twente, Vision Laboratory
POSITION HELD     Research Assistant
DESCRIPTION OF DUTIES
                  Employed by the University of Twente, in the Computer Vision
                  laboratory of the division 'Systems, Control and Computer
                  Engineering', faculty of Electrical Engineering, for the ESPRIT
                  project OS612/1593, with the following responsibilities:

                  o     Doing research (literature studies, modelling, experiments)
                        on the optical and visual factors involved in the perception
                        of computer generated images displayed in new Flat Panel
                        Display technologies.
                  o     Conducting verification experiments using at first a
                        simulator of the final equipment (an IIS image processor
                        model 75 connected to a Masscomp host computer). Later
                        carrying out ergonomic experiments with the ESPRIT
                        equipment itself.
                        Developing new low-level routines for controlling the IIS
                        image processor.
                  o     Writing reports and defending to the experts of ESPRIT
                        the results of said research, everything in the English
                        language.
                  o     Installation of the computer equipment for the project
                  o     Writing dedicated software and testing programs for the
                        advanced special hardware (achieving 15.000.000.000
                        operations per second)
                  o     Writing repair software to circumvent many bugs,
                        unavoidable in a first design.
                  o     Developing general purpose software for -amongst others-
                        connecting peripherals.
                  o     Writing manuals for the Display Simulator.
                  o     Maintaining the operating system of the simulator (Unix).
                  o     Co-operated in publications
                  o     Presented publication [2] at the symposium of the SID
                        (Society for Information Display) in may 1988.
                  o     Accompanying students at the numerous assignments
                        done for the project.

                  Gathered extensive knowledge of operating systems (especially
                  Unix), computer languages (C and Pascal), computer hardware
                  (existing like the IIS image processor or new like the prototype
                  hardware for the simulator), signal/data and image processing
                  and the human visual system during the project.

<h3>TECHNICAL REPORTS</h3>

            (1)   W.H. Bakker, "Software structure of the implementation of the
                  vision model", UTBSC ESPRIT OS 1593, 065.343 (1988)
            (2)   W.H. Bakker, "Report describing the model of different covers",
                  Part 1: "Display covers", Part 2: "Theory of reflections", UTBSC
                  ESPRIT OS 1593, 88V157 (1988)
            (3)   W.H. Bakker, "Aspects of coatings", UTBSC ESPRIT OS 1593,
                  89V004 (1989)
            (4)   W.H. Bakker, "On the choice of a model of luminance perception",
                  UTBSC ESPRIT 065.1894 (1986)
            (5)   H.L.M. van Huijstee and W.H. Bakker, "Software Manual of the
                  Simulator Machine", 1989, UTBSC 89M160.
            (6)   W.H. Bakker, "Computer Vision", lecture notes, Hogeschool
                  Utrecht, Industrial Automation and Computer Integrated
                  Manufacturing, 1992
            (7)   W.H. Bakker, "Remote Sensing Data and GIS Data on CD-ROM",
                  report for the BCRS, project Alexander II, nr. 6.4/IS-01, Work
                  Package 7, 1994
            (8)   W.H. Bakker, "The Internet - The World at your Fingertips", Internal
                  Technical ITC report, 1994
            (9)   W.H. Bakker, "Digital Image Processing Systems", lecture notes
                  for the DIP5/IGP3 course, ITC RSD 62, 1994

<h3>PUBLICATIONS</h3>

            [1]   D. Bosman, W.H. Bakker, "Conditioning of local signal to noise
                  ratio", in: Signal Processing III: Theories and Applications, I.T. Young
                  et al (editors), pp 861-864, Elsevier Science Publishers BV. (Amsterdam),
                  EURASIP 1986.
            [2]   W.H. Bakker, D. Bosman, "Engineering how we see a display",
                  International symposium, Digest of technical papers, pp 439-444,
                  California USA, SID 1988.
	    [3]   D. Bosman, W.H. Bakker, "Non-linear filtering to improve dexterity
	          in spatial control", Trans Inst MC, Vol 12 No 1, pp 44-48, 1990

<h3>PERSONS OF REFERENCE</h3>

                  Prof. Ir. N.J. Mulder   ITC               +31 53 874480
                  Prof. Ir. D. Bosman     Twente University +31 53 892780
                  Ir. H.L.M. van Huijstee IMIX              +31 53 836305



Enschede, July 1995
</pre>
<a href="mailto:bakker@itc.nl"><address>Wim Bakker</address></a>
