<HEAD><TITLE>Orbital Models and Element Sets</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<pre><img src="logo/itc.gif" alt="ITC">                                  <img src="logo/sealwhb.gif" alt="WHB"></pre>
<hr>
<H1>Orbital Models and Element Sets</H1>

<h2>Satellite Tracking Software</h2>
<ul>
<li> <a href="http://ssl.berkeley.edu/isi_www/sattrack.html">SatTrack WWW Home Page</a>
<li><a href="http://www.primenet.com/~bester/sattrack.html">SatTrack</a>

<li> <a href="ftp://plaza.aarnet.edu.au/micros/pc/SimTel/msdos/satelite/">TrakSat version 3.00</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.amsat.org/amsat/AmsatHome.html">TrakSat version 3.10</a>
<li> <a href="ftp://ftp.amsat.org/amsat/software/PC/tracking/trak310.zip">TrakSat version 3.10</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.jsci.com">PCTRACK, The Johnson Scientific International Universe</a>
<li><a href="http://www.physics.ox.ac.uk/sat/vsohp/orbsoft.html">More Satellite Prediction Software</a>
<li><a href="http://www.netwide.net/logsat/">LogSat</a>
<li><a href="http://seawifs.gsfc.nasa.gov/SEAWIFS/HRPT/SEATRACK.html">SeaWiFS Orbit Prediction Software Release (SeaTrack)</a>
<li><a href="http://ftp.amsat.org/amsat/intro/sats_faq.html">InstantTrack or QuickTrack</a> available from AMSAT
</ul>

<p>
<h2>Orbital Elements Sets</h2>
<ul>
<LI><A HREF=" http://www.grove.net/~tkelso/">Celestial WWW by Dr TS Kelso</A>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://nippori.tkl.iis.u-tokyo.ac.jp/pub/TBUS/">TBUS archive</A>
<li> <a href="ftp://archive.afit.af.mil/pub/space/tle.new"> Latest TLE's</a>
<li> <a href="ftp://archive.afit.af.mil/pub/space/archives/">Archive of TLE's</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://spacelink.msfc.nasa.gov/Instructional.Materials/Software/Tracking.Elements/">Spacelink: Tracking Elements</A>
<li> <a href="gopher://seds.lpl.arizona.edu/"> SEDS sat elements etc...</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.stk.com/files/agi/tle/">TLEs via Analytical Graphics</a>
</ul>

<p>
<h2>Orbital Models tutorials</h2>
<li><a href="http://www.amsat.org/amsat/keps/kepmodel.html">Keplerian Elements Tutorial</a> on <a href="http://www.amsat.org/">AMSAT</a>
<li><a href="http://www.physics.ox.ac.uk/sat/vsohp/getkeps.html">More Sources of orbital data</a>
<li><a href="http://www.alcyone.com/max/physics/kepler/index.html">Kepler's laws</a>
</ul>

<p>
<h2>Miscellaneous</h2>
<ul>
<li> <a href="ftp://ftp.std.com/pub/Clyde/">Programs for coverage grid of Lansat, IRS and SPOT</a>
<LI><A HREF="ftp://services.esrin.esa.it/pub/desc">ERS coverage program</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.eosat.com/EOS/IMAGE/dwrsmap.html">Path and Row of Landsat-TM, IRS-1B LISS-1, IRS-1B LISS-2, and IRS-P2 LISS-2</A>

<p>
<li><a href="http://ssl.berkeley.edu/isi_www/satpasses.html">SatPasses Home Page</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.acs.ncsu.edu/scripts/HamRadio/sattrack.perl">Satellite Tracking Prediction Gateway</a>
<li> <a href="http://www-leland.stanford.edu/~iburrell/sat/sattrack.html">Satellite Observering Resources</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.rzg.mpg.de/~bdp/vsohp/satintro.html"><b>Visual</b> Satellite Observer's Home Page</a>
<li> <a href="http://www.chara.gsu.edu/sat.html">Earth Satellite Ephemeris Service</a>, fill in a form for a prediction of visible satellites.
</ul>

