<h2>Netfind</h2>

NetFind can be used for a lookup of a person's e-mail address. Use it 
sparsely and only if other means fail!
<ul>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@archie.au">AARNet, Melbourne, Australia</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@bruno.cs.colorado.edu">University of Colorado, Boulder</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@dino.conicit.ve">Nat. Council for Techn. & Scien. Research, Venezuela</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@ds.internic.net">InterNIC Directory and DB Services, S. Plainfield, NJ</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@lincoln.technet.sg">Technet Unit, Singapore</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@malloco.ing.puc.cl">Catholic University of Chile, Santiago</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@monolith.cc.ic.ac.uk">Imperial College, London, England</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@mudhoney.micro.umn.edu">University of Minnesota, Minneapolis</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@netfind.anu.edu.au">Australian National University, Canberra</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@netfind.ee.mcgill.ca">McGill University, Montreal, Quebec, Canada</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@netfind.if.usp.br">University of Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@netfind.oc.com">OpenConnect Systems, Dallas, Texas</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@netfind.vslib.cz">Liberec University of Technology, Czech Republic</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@nic.nm.kr">Korea Network Information Center, Taejon, Korea</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@nic.uakom.sk">Academy of Sciences, Banska Bystrica, Slovakia</a>
<li><a href="telnet://netfind@redmont.cis.uab.edu">University of Alabama at Birmingham</a>

</ul>

