<h1>Preface</h1>
This report was conducted under contract of the BCRS (BeleidsCommissie
Remote Sensing, or the Dutch Coordination Committee for Remote Sensing).
It is part of the Alexander project. Alexander is the educational Image
Processing package for Remotely Sensed images developed by the ITC.
Originally it was developed for the Archimedes (by Acorn) computers.
Currently there is also a port for PCs. The PC version was implemented
by a Dutch company called CSL.
<p>
One of the workpackages of the project comprises the creation of a CD-ROM containing
example data sets that could be used in exercises within Alexander. It was
soon discovered that RS data is expensive and copyright issues are tricky.
So instead the workpackage was changed to making a report on RS data sets
readily available.
<p>
This reports describes
<ul>
<li>the most common satellite platforms
<li>the CD-ROM family
<li>the Kodak Photo CD
<li>available data sets
<li>addresses of organizations that supply these data sets
<li>etc. etc...
</ul>
All in all it contains a wealth of information on the field of Remote Sensing
and GIS.
<p>
<i>Wim Bakker</i>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT10-B02-255</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA019-000202-B010-16</DOCOLDNO>
