<h1>CD-ROM Drives and <a href="#section 2">Recorders</a></h1>

<h2>CD-ROM Drives</h2>

The most highly recommended drive is the Toshiba 3401. It is a very fast and very
reliable drive. It is reasonably priced, but you will also need to buy a SCSI controller.
<p>
The NEC CD-ROM drives 336,37,73,74,83, etc. have received many favourable
recommendations.
<p>
<a name="drives">Table 4</a>. <strong>Information on a number of CD-ROM Drives.   </strong>
<p>
Column:
<dl>
<dt><strong>A</strong>.   Manufacturer
<dt><strong>B</strong>.   Model Number
<dt><strong>C</strong>.   Internal/External/Both
<dt><strong>D</strong>.   Caddies <dd>N=No, S=Sony, P=Philips, X=NEC, O=Other
<dt><strong>E</strong>.   Seek time in milliseconds
<dt><strong>F</strong>.   Transfer rate in kilobytes/second
<dt><strong>G</strong>.   SCSI - N/Y/2-scsi 2
<dt><strong>H</strong>.   CDROM XA / PhotoCD compatible <dd>(N=No, S=Single-Session, M=multi-session)
<dt><strong>I</strong>.   OS/2 Compatible - Y/N
<dt><strong>J</strong>.   Windows NT Compatible - Y/N
<dt><strong>K</strong>.   MPC Compatible - Y/N
<dt><strong>L</strong>.   Quicktime Compatible - Y/N
<dt><strong>N</strong>.   Approximate Street Price, in US dollars
<dt><strong>O</strong>.   Yes/No/Recommended/- not reviewed
<dt><strong>Q</strong>.   Comments
</dl>
<pre>
