<h2>IPL Equipment</h2>

<h3>Hardware</h3>
<ul>
<li>3 HP9000s720's, HP-UX 9.01, one 8 bit screen, two 24 true color screens
<li>1 HP on loan from the ILWIS group
<li>Sun Sparcstation 2, SunOS 4.1.3
<li>Sun 3, SunOS 4.1
<li>Several PC's, two with NFS
<li>Several Acorn Archimedes systems, RiscOS
<li>
<li>
<li>
<li>PDP 11/44, RSX 11 (out of maintenance)
</ul>
All computers are connected to Ethernet, which gives a flexible processing
environment.
<hr>

<h3>Image Processing Hardware</h3>
<ul>
<li>Context Vision, GOP & BOP
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>Peripherals</h3>
<ul>
<li>more than 10 gigabytes of disc space
<li>2 HP XWindow terminals
<br>
1 XWindow terminal on loan to the ILWIS group
<li>Optronics C-4300 filmwriter
<br>
For slides/negatives up to 10 by 10 inch, resolution 25/50/100 micrometer per pixel
<li>Calcomp 31
<br>
For 35mm slides
<li>Shinko 645 termal wax color printer
<li>HP Laserjet 4, 600 dpi
<li>Sharp JX-300, A4 300 dpi color scanner
<li>DAT drive
<li>EXABYTE drive
<li>CD-ROM drive
<li>Magneto-Optical drive, 2x 600 Mb
<li>CCT drive, table-top 6250 bpi
<li>QIC drive, 150 Mb
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>Software</h3>
To name a few
<ul>
<li><b>Erdas</b> 7.5
<li><b>Imagine</b> 8.1
<li><b>Arc/Info</b>
<li><b>Ilwis</b>, Integrated Land and Watershed Information System
<br>
Image Processing & GIS software for PC, developed by ITC
<li><b>Alexander</b>
<br>
Image Processing software for Archimedes, developed by ITC
<li><b>IDL</b>, Interactive Data Language
<li><b>Perl</b> 4.036, Unix script language
<li><b>SIPS</b>, Spectral Image Processing System
<li>gcc, GNU's C-language compiler
<li><b>Khoros</b>
<br>
The extensive Image Processing package/User Interface by the University
of New Mexico
<li><b>ProdiGeo</b>
<br>
A georeference/database software package for satellite images by MATRA
<li>
Many Public Domain/Shareware/GNU packages for
Image Processing and Graphics and other things
<br>
xv, xfig, xpaint, gzip, zip, etc...
<li>Internet Service Clients/Servers
<br>
Mosaic, httpd, lynx, xarchie, xgopher, nn, wu-ftpd etc...
<li><b>DMS</b>, Desktop Mapping System
<br>
For creating ortho-images and DEM's (Digital Elevation Models) from
aerial photographs and SPOT satellite images
<li>PROJ 4.3, carthographic projection software from the USGS
<li>SatTrack V2.0, Satellite Tracking software
</ul>

