<BODY>
<H1><CENTER>RESOLUTION</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
The industrial hygiene organizations (ACGIH, AIHA, ABIH/AAIH) agree to appoint
two Board members each to an integrating team, by November 1, 1996, to address the
following issues, as they relate to consolidation:
<P>
1.  Protection of TLVs; and,
2.  Representation of minority members (e.g., governmental) in public policy statements and
positions; and,
3.  Adequate representation of professional groups (e.g., governmental ) on elected Boards.
<P>
The integrating team will be supported financially and administratively by each organization
equally (ABIH/AAIH will be treated as one organization).  If the three issues previously
identified can be resolved, the integrating team will provide a revised consolidated model for
Board vote within an <I>estimated</I> time period of 90-270 days.  In any case, the
organizations and/or their successors agree to work toward increasing cooperation for the benefit
of the profession.
<P>
If the Boards agree to the revised model, each will submit this by common ballot to their
memberships for a vote.
<P>
<A HREF="index.html">Back to AIHA Home Page</A>
</BODY>
