<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIHA Membership</TITLE>

<H1>Membership Information</H1>
<BR>
<H2>AIHA National Membership</H2>
The American Industrial Hygiene Association, founded in 1939, is an organization of
professionals dedicated to the prevention of workplace-related illness or injury. With more
than 11,000 members, AIHA is the largest international association serving the needs of
occupational and environmental scientists and engineers practicing industrial hygiene.
<P>
The purposes of AIHA are to promote the field of industrial hygiene, to provide education
and training, to provide a forum for the exchange of ideas and information, and to represent
the interests of industrial hygienists and those they serve.
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="benefits.html">Membership Benefits</A>
<LI><A HREF="category.html">Categories of Membership</A>
<LI><A HREF="liabilit.html"> Professional Liability Insurance</A>
</UL>
<!--Add Later: Membership Survey Results, Membership Directory (Members Only)-->

<B><I>Need an application form? Call AIHA Support Services at 703-849-8888, or our InfoFax
Service at 703-641-INFO and request document number 1001.</B></I>
<HR>
<H2>Local Section Membership</H2>
<I>Local section</I> is the term used by AIHA to designate regional chapters.
<P>
Membership in an AIHA local section provides you with a wide range of networking
opportunities in the occupational health field.
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="./sections/sections.html">Local Section Listing</A>
<LI><A HREF="./sections/council.html">Local Section Council</A>
<LI><A HREF="./sections/support.html">AIHA Support for Local Sections</A>
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<H2>AIHA Organizational Members</H2>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.unitedsales.com">United Sales Associates</A>
</UL>
<P>
