<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIHA Committee Information</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1>Committee Information</H1>
Committee members are the architects of the association structure. They plan, develop, and
institute many of the association projects, including position statements, continuing education
courses, publications, and technical and roundtable sessions presented at various conferences.
<P>
Involvement in AIHA technical committees offers members the opportunity to share a wealth
of knowledge and expertise, and those who serve on AIHA's technical committees are
awarded certification maintenance points (CMP's).
<P>
Committee membership is open to all AIHA national members. Individuals interested in
serving on specific committees should direct a letter of interest, including background and
experience, to the chairs of the specific committees.
<HR>
<A HREF="./committe/task.html">Task Forces</A>
<HR>
