<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIHA Continuing Education</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="pdp.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="[PDP Logo]"> 
<H1>AIHA Continuing Education</H1>
AIHA is committed to helping provide its members and other professionals with the tools
they need to reach their goals through continuing education. These needs continually unfold
as the profession evolves and AIHA responds with corresponding courses and publications.
<HR>

<H1>1997 Professional Development Schedule</H1>
<H2>Course Schedule </H2>
<B>Fundamentals of Industrial Hygiene</B><BR>
February 24-28, 1997 | San Diego, California<BR>
June 23-27, 1997 | Atlanta, Georgia<BR>
October 6-10, 1997 | Seattle, Washington<BR>
This introductory course provides a practical understanding of industrial hygiene principles and
practices. 
It will also familiarize participants with the terminology and basic concepts of health hazard
recognition,
evaluation, and control methods.<BR>
Price: $955 AIHA Member, $1095 Nonmember
<P>
<B>Quantitative Industrial Hygiene</B><BR>
March 24-27, 1997 | Cleveland, Ohio<BR>
August 11-14, 1997 | Cleveland, Ohio <BR>
This course provides the ability to calibrate and use standard industrial hygiene air sampling
equipment as well as noise and heat stress monitoring instrumentation.  Daily lab sessions,
problem sets, and small breakout groups allow for thorough understanding of concepts.<BR>
Price: $855 AIHA Member, $995 Nonmember
<P>
<B>Comprehensive Industrial Hygiene Exam Review</B><BR>
<I>cosponsored by the University of Michigan and the Michigan Industrial Hygiene
Society</I><BR>
March 18-21, 1997 | Ann Arbor, Michigan <BR>
September 8-11, 1997 | Ann Arbor, Michigan <BR>
This course is designed for those who are studying for the ABIH industrial hygiene certification
exam. This course provides excellent reference materials, problem-solving exercises, and daily
computer labs, with software specifically developed for CIH exam review.<BR>
Price: $955 AIHA Member, $1095 Nonmember
<P>
<P>
<H2>Symposium Schedule</H2>
<B>Information Technology Symposium = Facing New Challenges/Finding New
Solutions</B><BR>
<I>to be held in conjunction with the American Industrial Hygiene Conference &
Exposition</I><BR>
May 17, 1997 | Dallas, Texas
<P>
<B>Indoor Air Quality Symposium Current Practices Around the World</B>
<I>to be held in conjunction with the American Industrial Hygiene Conference &
Exposition</I><BR>
May 18, 1997 | Dallas, Texas
<P>
<B>Promoting Occupational Hygiene Through Partnerships in Research</B><BR>
August 7-8, 1997 | Washington, DC
<P>
<B>12th Annual Toxicology Symposium</B><BR>
July 27-31, 1997 | Seattle, Washington
<P>
<B>Risk Assessment Symposium</B><BR>
September 25-26, 1997 | Baltimore, Maryland
<P>
<B>5th Annual International Hazard Communication Symposium</B><BR>
September 1997 | TBA
<P>
<B>2nd Annual Consultants Symposium</B><BR>
Fall of 1997 | TBA
<P>
For more information about AIHA professional development programs, contact the Continuing
Education Department at (703) 849-8888, e-mail 
<A HREF="mailto:infonet@aiha.org">infonet@aiha.org</A>, or try
AIHA's InfoFax fax-on-demand service at (703) 641-INFO.
