<IMG SRC="graphics/lablogo.gif">
<HEAD>
<TITLE>AIHA Laboratory Accreditation Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
When a laboratory participates in one or more of AIHA's laboratory programs, it has solid
credentials from the association that has symbolized integrity in accreditation for more than 20
years.  AIHA programs help organizations improve the excellence of their laboratories and
provide a measure of quality assurance. The AIHA seal of approval shows that your laboratory is
capable of achieving and maintaining the highest level of professional performance.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR> 
<H2>Accreditation Programs</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="ihlap1.html">Industrial Hygiene Laboratory Accreditation
(IHLAP) Program</A> is for laboratories involved in analyzing samples to evaluate workplace
exposure.
<LI>The <A HREF="ellap1.html">Environmental Lead Laboratory Accreditation
(ELLAP) Program</A> is designed for laboratories involved in the analysis of environmental
lead
samples.
<LI>The <A HREF="aar1.html">Asbestos Analysts Registry (AAR)</A> is a program for
analysts
involved in asbestos fiber counting of air samples.
</UL>
<HR>
<H2>Performance Testing Programs</H2>
<UL>
<LI>The analytes for the <A HREF="pat1.html">Proficiency Analytical Testing
(PAT) Program</A> include: metals, silica, asbestos and solvents and is provided on a quarterly
basis. 
<LI>The <A HREF="elpat1.html">Environmental Lead Proficiency Analytical Testing
(ELPAT) Program</A> provides paint chip, soil, air and dust wipe analysis on a quarterly basis.
<LI>The <A HREF="bulk1.html">Bulk Asbestos Proficiency Analytical Testing
(BAPAT) Program</A> provides bulk building materials on a regularly scheduled basis.
<LI>The <A HREF="aat1.html">Asbestos Analytical Testing (AAT) Program</A> are
aerosol generated samples provided on a quarterly basis.
<LI><IMG SRC="newd.gif"><A HREF="new.html"> Testing Programs</A>
</UL>
<HR>
<H2>List of Accredited Laboratories</H2>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="labstate.html">U.S. Industrial Hygiene Accredited Labs by State</A>
<LI><A HREF="labalpha.html">U.S. Industrial Hygiene Accredited Labs - Alphabetical
Listing</A>
<LI><A HREF="foreign.html">International Industrial Hygiene Accredited Labs by
Country</A>
<LI><A HREF="ellapsta.html">ELLAP Accredited Laboratories</A>
<BR>
<LI><A HREF="aarapp.html">Asbestos Analyst Registry (AAR) Approved Organizations</A>
</UL>
<HR>
<BR>
<H2>News and Updates</H2>
<A HREF="com.html"><IMG SRC="rbutton.gif"></A><B>   Information on meetings
related to lab accreditation.</B><BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="nllapinf.html"><IMG SRC="rbutton.gif"></A><B>   402/404 C - Final Rule
published.</B><BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="clia.html"><IMG SRC="rbutton.gif"></A><B>   Biological Monitoring & the
Clinical
Laboratory Improvement Act (CLIA) of 1988.</B><BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="fax.html"><IMG SRC="rbutton.gif"></A><B>   Applications and fees for all
laboratory programs.</B>
<BR>
