AIHA's New Guide </A>
<LI><A HREF="pr7.html"> AIHA Publishes One-of-a-Kind Management Book With an
Occupational Health and Safety Perspective</A></UL></LI>
<P>
<HR>
<H2>Operation Outreach</H2>
"Operation Outreach: Taking Industrial Hygiene Issues to the Community" contains valuable
information that we will help you and the industrial hygiene profession gain recognition within
the community.
<P>
The kit includes sample press releases, fact sheets, presentation tips, and more. An
accompanying color slide presentation on environmental lead and indoor air quality is available
for loan to AIHA members. Tips on speaking to student groups and hints on becoming a better
exhibitor are included, and there is
a section on creating a local section newsletter. In addition, we have color career transparencies
available for presentations at career fairs or schools.
<P>
This program is free for AIHA members.
Call (703) 849-8888 or E-mail your request:<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:cfeheley@aiha.org">Christine Feheley</A><BR>
<P>
For additional information about AIHA consumer brochures, please see the Community
Involvement Resources section of the Publications Catalog.
