<TITLE>AIHCE 97 Conference Information</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="graphics/97logo.gif"align="left"ALT="[AIHCE  97 Logo]"><BR>
<H1>American Industrial Hygiene Conference &amp; Exposition</H1>
<H2>AIHCE 1997:<BR>
Taking Responsibility: Building Tomorrow's Profession</H2>
In 1997, AIHCE will be held May 17-23 at the Dallas Convention Center in Dallas.  
Members of AIHA and ACGIH will receive registration information by mail. Nonmembers may
call (703) 849-8888 or e-mail <A HREF="mailto:infonet@aiha.org">infonet@aiha.org</A> for
registration information.<BR>
<P>
<UL><LI><A HREF="abstract.html">1997 AIHCE Call for Abstracts (Platform and Poster
Presentations) Instructions</A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="aihce97/abform.html">1997 AIHCE Abstract Submission Form</A></UL>

<H3>Announcement and Call for Notice of Interest</H3>
Cosponsored by the American Industrial Hygiene Association and the American Conference of
Governmental Industrial Hygienists
<P>
Recognizing that occupational and environmental health and safety is at a crossroads, do you
count yourself as one of the profession's new pioneers? Evaluating the horizon, are you willing to
seize the opportunity to shape the future of the profession, to anticipate the right directions?
<P>
<H4>Professional Development Courses</H4>
More than 100 PDCs on critical occupational health and safety issues taught by experts in the
field.
<P> 
<H4>Keynote Speakers</H4>
National and international experts give presentations followed by breakout roundtable
discussions where participation and questions are encouraged.
<P>
<H4>Value-packed technical program including:</H4>
<LI> Platform Sessions
<LI> Roundtables
<LI> Case Studies
<LI> Poster Sessions

<H4>Exposition</H4>
The largest occupational health and safety expo featuring the latest products and services with
opportunity for hands-on demonstrations.
<P>
The American Industrial Hygiene Association (AIHA) and American Conference of
Governmental Industrial Hygienists, Inc., (ACGIH) are sponsors of the American Industrial
Hygiene Conference & Exposition (AIHCE).
<P>
The AIHCE is the premier scientific meeting, as well as, one of the largest expositions of
equipment and services for occupational and environmental health professionals in the world. 
The AIHCE attracts approximately 10,000 attendees annually with 450 exhibiting 
organizations using 86,000 net sq. of exhibit space.
<P>
Exhibitors at the AIHCE provide products and services/consulting services which aid and assist
in the protection of the health and safety of workers and the community. 
<P>
<H4>Social Activities</H4>
A chance to network and mingle with your peers. Activities that are designed to expand your
circle of colleagues and friends.
<P>
<H4>Here are just a few of the AIHCE '97 topics:</H4>
<LI> Future Technology in the Profession
<LI> Professional Ethics
<LI> Indoor Air Quality
<LI> Consulting in the Profession
<LI> Aerosols
<LI> Exposure Assessment Strategies
<LI> Management Issues
<LI> Standards of Good Practice
<LI> Ergonomics
<LI> OSHA Reform
<LI> Hazardous Waste
<LI> Regulatory and Policy Issues
<LI> International Occupational Hygiene Issues

<H4>Contact AIHA Support Services at (703) 849-8888 for more information on the
following:</H4>
<LI> <A HREF="aihce97/abform.html">Abstract Submission Forms</A>
<LI> Roundtable Submission Forms
<LI> Professional Development Courses
<LI> Exhibit Space
<LI> Advertising/Sponsorship Opportunities
<LI> Registration Information (starting February 1997)
<P>
<H4>Fax lines are open 24 hours a day! (703) 207-3561</H4>
<DL>
<DT>July 1, 1996 <DD><A HREF="abstract.html">Call for Abstracts,</A> Roundtables, and
Case Studies mailed
<DT>August 15, 1996 <DD>Deadline for professional development course abstract submissions
<DT>October 17, 1996 <DD>Deadline for abstract, roundtable, and case study submissions
<DT>November 4, 1996 <DD>Permanent conference committee meets
<DT>November 22, 1996 <DD>Deadline for function requests for 1997 Advance Program
<DT>December 3, 1996 <DD>Permanent conference committee meets
<DT>December 4, 1996 <DD>Session arrangers meeting
<DT>February 7, 1997 <DD>Advance Program mailed
<DT>February 21, 1997 <DD>Deadline for function requests for Final Program
</DL>
<BR>
