<P>
<H1>AIHCE EXPO</H1>
<H2>May 20 to May 22, 1997</H2>
<B>Dallas Convention Center<BR>
Dallas, Texas</B>
<P>
<B><I>Your competitors know the value of AIHCE in achieving their marketing and sales
objectives.</B></I>
<H2>Shouldn't you be there, too?</H2>
<P>
<I>1997 American Industrial Hygiene Conference & Exposition<BR>
Sponsored by the American Industrial Hygiene Association (AIHA)<BR>
and the American Conference of Governmental Industrial Hygienists (ACGIH)</I>
<P>
<B>Exhibit at AIHCE . . . </B>where the most influential buyers of the industrial hygiene,
occupational and environmental health and safety products and services gather.
<P>
<B>Industrial hygienists look to AIHCE</B> for cutting-edge technology, breakthrough ideas
and the best in provider networking.  Exhibit at AIHCE and benefit from the buying power of our
10,000 loyal attendees.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<H2>Quick facts on the purchasing power of AIHCE attendees:</H2>
<B><I>92%</B></I> of AIHCE attendees have purchase influence and the ability to select your
products and services.<BR>
<B><I>79%</B></I> of 1996 AIHCE attendees surveyed plan to buy or recommend a purchase
of products seen at the exposition.<BR>
<B><I>31%</B></I> of AIHCE attendees make purchases on the $50,000 to over $100,000
range our attendees are responsible for major capital outlays.<BR>
<B><I>Over half</B></I> of AIHCE attendees work for firms with 500 to over 5,000
employees firms most likely to invest in the latest products and services.<BR>
<B><I>67%</B></I> of AIHCE attendees are managers and technicians significant members of
any firm's buying team.<BR>
<B><I>97%</B></I> of AIHCE attendees serve in functional areas of occupational and
environmental health and safety your target market for industrial hygiene equipment, products
and services.<BR>
<P>
<HR>
<H2>NEW for 1997</H2>
<B>The AIHCE Technology Pavilion</B><BR>
The AIHCE Technology Pavilion is designed to spotlight cutting-edge technology and services
in the occupational and environmental health and safety industry. Over 5,500 prime square feet
of exposition floor space is reserved, decorated and promoted to ensure high attendee traffic. All
high-tech solutions, whether computer hardware, software, or complete turn-key application
systems, will benefit from the focused attention this exclusive area provides.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER><B>AIHCE exhibitors benefit from a growing qualified attendee base with proven
buying power. Don't miss out on this valuable marketplace.
<P>
Help your new customers find you not your competition. Send for more information on
exhibiting at AIHCE.
<P>
If you are interested in additional information or would like to sign up to exhibit at the 
1997 AIHCE Expo, please contact Bart Ecker, exhibits coordinator, at (703) 849-8888 
or by e-mail at <A HREF="mailto:becker@aiha.org">becker@aiha.org.</A>
<P>
To receive a copy of the 1997 AIHCE application for exhibit space and floor plan of 
available booths by fax, please call (703) 641-4636, follow the instructions, and request 
document numbers 3803 and 3805.</B></CENTER>
<HR>
