<head>
<title>AIHA Board of Directors Meeting</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><h1>Board of Directors Meeting</h1>
<b>May 19, 1996<BR>
Grand Hyatt - Washington, D.C.</b></center>
<HR>

<H3>Officers Attending:</H3>
Z. Mansdorf, V. Rose, J. Burton, J. Thornton, L. Anderson, J. Lynch

<h3>Directors Attending:</h3>
D. Bissonnette, P. Brogan, W. Dyson, M. Herr, J. Lee, G. McCluskey, A. Nichting, D. Reid, 
U. Wright, S. Wroblewski

<h3>Guests:</h3>
S. Shattuck, LSC Chair, R. Coyne, LSC Vice Chair, H. Muranko, S. Levine, T. Grumbles, D.
Doganiero, P. Lubs, J. Singh, J. Rock, H. Ettinger, Mr. Ganak (US Navy), J. Martyny (IEQ
Chair)

<h3>Staff:</h3>
O. G. Banks, B. Morrison, D. Ethier, C. Tobin, J. Lawrence, A. Dees, M. Gomez, A. Trippler
<HR>
<p>
<h3>1. Call to Order/Quorum Verification</h3>
President Rose called the meeting to order at 9:00 a.m.  Secretary Thornton confirmed
quorum present.
<p>
<h3>2. Secretary's Report - Thornton</h3>
Thornton reviewed the minutes of the March 14, 1996 Board meeting and the Executive
Committee conference call minutes of May 13, 1996.
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Accept the minutes of the March 14, 1996 Board meeting as amended. 
Passed.
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Adopt and ratify the results of Mail Ballots 96-093 and 96-100 and any votes
by telephone occurring since last Board meeting.  Passed.
<p>
The Board discussed ballot 96-099 on changing the benefits offered to Level II Organizational
Members.  The bylaws were reviewed.  As this ballot did not follow the bylaws of AIHA, it was
determined to not be an official ballot; therefore, it was withdrawn.  The Membership Committee
Chair will be directed to develop and submit recommendations to the Board for discussion at the
August Board meeting.

<p>
Action Item List Update - Each Action Item was reviewed and new due dates set, status report
given, new assignments made and completed items deleted. .
<p>
Board agreed to sunset the OHSMS Task Force and assign responsibility for updating OHSMS
to the Management Committee.
<p>
<h3>3. Treasurer's Report - Anderson</h3>

A brief overview of the April financial statements was given.  Current AIHCE registration is
7396; 856 booth spaces sold.  PDC registrations were down about 500 from 1995.
<p>
<h3>4. Unification Discussion - Rose</h3>

<b>MOTION:</b> Accept the UTF Report.  Passed.
<p>
A meeting with the top two officers and the executive directors of the four organizations will be
held at 5:30 p.m. May 19, 1996.  A reprint of the Executive Summary of the UTF Report will be
in the June/July Synergist.
<p>
There was further discussion of unification as to how to present concept to the membership, how
the balloting would be completed, etc.  Various questions and suggestions were raised including;
Bylaws review/change re: AIHA dissolution.  (Banks to contact Attorney Herold regarding
bylaw change/AIHA dissolution.)  Should a comment section be put on the ballot to members? 
Will there be a public forum to allow membership to comment on unification?  Local Section
communications should include newsletters, AIHCE meeting, etc.  
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> AIHA supports the concept of one industrial hygiene organization.  Passed.   
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Send an opinion ballot to the voting members expressing the Board's
preference for unification.  Passed.
<p>
<h3>12. MSDS In Electronic Commerce Presentation - Thornton/Ganak</h3>

Mr. Ganak presented the Navy's recommendations on using electronic transmission of MSDS
rather than paper citing the various pluses, etc. and encouraged AIHA to promote this concept.
<p>
<h3>5. Student Local Section of the Year Award - Mansdorf</h3>

<b>MOTION:</b> Approve the development of Student Local Section of the Year Award
which will include $1000 and a plaque sponsored by the AIHA.  Passed.
<p>
<h3>6. Conflict of Interest and Antitrust Policies - McCluskey</h3>

Discussion of the need for Conflict of Interest and Antitrust Policies and review of material from
Attorney Herold.  Motion presented on agenda was amended.

<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Adopt an antitrust policy.  Passed
<p>
<h3>7. Joint Task Group on Occupational Exposure Database - Herr</h3>

<b>MOTION:</b>  Recommend the adoption of the recommendations in this guidance
document, to be used by practitioners and institutions who collect, organize, retain and use
workplace exposure data.  Passed.
<p>
<h3>8. Eureka Laboratory Accreditation - Thornton</h3>

Item withdrawn as the Executive Committee handled it during May 13, 1996 conference call.
<p>
<h3>9. Travel Expense Guidelines - Anderson</h3>

These travel expense guidelines are to be included in the Committee Chair's Manual for 1997.
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Accept the travel guidelines as presented.  Passed.
<p>
By consensus the Board approved required receipts for expenses over $25.
<p>
<h3>10. Update Priority Issues - Burton</h3>

PEL Task Force is headed by J. Lynch and has no members assigned as of yet.  Ethical Conduct
of IH Professionals should be removed from the priority list.  Work will take place on this as
required, rather than as a permanent priority.
<p>
<h3>11. Top 10 Committee Awards - Nichting</h3>

After a brief discussion it was decided that this item will be placed on the August 1996 meeting
agenda.  Any comments and feedback are due to Nichting by July 15 so they may included with
the agenda packet for August.
<p>
<h3>13. Annual Report on IOHA Activities - Lee/Ettinger</h3>

Ettinger distributed a printed report on the meeting in the United Kingdom and briefly
summarized the handout. 
<p>
<b>MOTION: Approve $5000 for an AIHA session to support the IOHA meeting in Switzerland
on International Standards and Occupational Hygiene.  Passed.</b>
<p>
<h3>14. Standards of Good Practice Task Force - Burton</h3>

Burton gave a brief overview of current Task Force activity.
<p>
<h3>15. AIHCE Contract Update - Banks</h3>

Banks reviewed the background of the situation and discussed the letters sent and received.  In
August 1995 a proposal was sent to ACGIH.  They did not respond until 2 weeks before the
1996 AIHCE.  They want the 1994 AIHCE records opened or AIHA pay about $50,000 to them
from the 1994 AIHCE.  AIHA stated, "No."  Banks and ACGIH Executive Director Strano will
meet after AIHCE to work on a new contract.
<p>
<h3>16. Indoor Air  96 Financial Support - Reid/J. Martyny</h3>

Reid and Martyny requested funds for 3 persons' travel and registration to attend Indoor Air  96
in Japan.  Partial funding has been obtained by the 3 persons, but additional funds are being
requested for this trip.
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Allocate an additional $1600 to Indoor Environmental Quality Committee
budget for funding this trip.  Passed.
<p>
<h3>17. Update of Activities with Technical Committees - Burton</h3>

Work is continuing on ways to improve the productivity of the technical committees.  Document
has been sent out to Board for comments.
<p>
<b>INFORMATION REPORTS</b>
<p>
<h3>18. Task Force List Update - Rose</h3>

<h3>19. President's Report - Rose</h3>

<h3>20. President-elect's Report - Mansdorf </h3>

Announced Board meetings.  Boston, Arrive August 19, meet 20 and 21, depart 21 with no
lunch.  December at Singer Island, FL, arrive 16, meet 17 and adjourn by 4:00 p.m. 
<p>
<h3>21. Vice-President's Report - Burton</h3>

<h3>22. Executive Director's Report - Banks</h3>

<h3>23. Consent Agenda - Committee Reports</h3>

<h3>24. Consent Agenda - Local Section Reports</h3>

<b>MOTION:</b> Accept the Committee and Local Section Reports as presented.  Passed.
<p>
<h3>25. Old Business - All</h3>

Wroblewski reported that CLEARCorp project is on track.  4 labs are doing gratis samples.
<p>
<h3>26. New Business - All</h3>

McCluskey indicated that denying lab accreditation should be done by the full board in a
meeting or by the Executive Committee.  The Board concurred by consensus.
<p>
<h3>Meeting was adjourned at 4:00 p.m.</h3>
<P>
<BR>
