<head>
<title>AIHA Board of Directors Meeting</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><h1>Board of Directors Meeting</h1>
<b>May 24, 1996<BR>
Grand Hyatt - Washington, D.C.</b></center>
<HR>

<H3>Officers Attending:</H3>
Z. Mansdorf, J. Burton, J. Rock, V. Rose, J. Thornton, B. Dyson

<h3>Directors Attending:</h3>
P. Brogan, D. Doganiero, T. Grumbles, M. Herr, P. Lubs, G. McCluskey, A. Nichting, J. Singh,
U. Wright, S. Wroblewski

<h3>Guests:</h3>
R. Coyne, LSC Chair, T. Cator, Lobbyist, A. Herold, Attorney, R. Kaufman, D. Harvey
(Emerging Issues Committee)

<h3>Staff:</h3>
O. G. Banks, B. Morrison, D. Ethier, C. Tobin, A. Trippler, A. Dees, J. Lawrence
<HR>
<p>
<h3>1.Call to Order/Quorum Verification - Mansdorf/Thornton</h3>
President Mansdorf called the meeting to order at 8:30 a.m.  Secretary Thornton confirmed
quorum present.

<h3>2. Secretary's Report - Thornton</h3>
The minutes of the May 19, 1996 meeting have not been prepared.  They will be presented at the
August 1996 Board meeting along with the minutes of May 24, 1996.  Record of Actions will be
prepared and submitted with the August meeting material.  Thornton gave a verbal report of the
June 21, 1996 Joint AIHA/ACGIH Executive Committee meeting.

<h3>3. Treasurer's Report - Dyson</h3>
No financial reports were presented.  Dyson indicated 3 situations that may affect the AIHA
finances:
<dl><dd>a) ACGIH/AIHA contract on the AIHCE</DD>
<dd>b) Unification</dd>
<dd>c) Proposal for ABIH cutting Certification Maintenance points for AIHCE</dd></dl>
President appointed Dyson and L. Anderson as a task force regarding AIHCE certification points
issued by ABIH.

<h3>4. Update of Activities with Technical Committees - Rock</h3>

Rock reported that committee productivity has improved as a result of the AIHA Strategic Plan. 
Committees are being advised of the request for Journal articles from committees.

<h3>5. Report of Government Affairs Activity - T. Cator</h3>
Cator reported that AIHA has been effective in some areas such as being asked to provide
testimony on OSHA.  R. Reich speaking at the AIHCE shows the impact AIHA has had.  AIHA
must continue to build trust relationships with Congress, through staff and members who will
come and talk face-to-face to Congress and staffers.

<h3>8. Conflict of Interest - A. Herold</h3>
Attorney Herold reported that the sample Conflict of Interest policy he submitted was in response
to Executive Director Banks.  Interpretation of the issue of Competing Organizations (#6) means
that information learned in one's capacity as a Board member.  It should remain within AIHA.  It
does not prohibit membership, etc. with competing organizations.  As to Board members
teaching courses; the association cannot request Board members refrain from earning a living by
teaching these courses, but a potential conflict of interest could be present.  Conflict of Interest
policy can apply as far down the organization as the Board wishes, but usually applies only to
officers and directors.
<p>
A question was raised regarding antitrust areas on pricing discussion.  Herold advised that any
discussion of price fixing or even the implication of such may be viewed as antitrust.
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Adopt a Conflict of Interest policy for AIHA.Withdrawn
<p>
Wright and Lee will work on a draft Conflict of Interest policy tailored to the AIHA Board.<br>
Herold gave an update on ethics case stating that 4 depositions are to be taken later this
summer.
<p>
Herold advised that as AIHA bylaws do not state how disposal of net worth would happen
should consolidation occur, the Illinois not-for-profit law would apply.  That law reads that all
debts must be paid and then the remaining assets may go to a for-profit or not-for-profit
organization.

<h3>7. ABIH Nominations/Candidates - Rose</h3>
This item will be on the August agenda.  Rose will provide candidate names at that time.

<h3>CLOSED SESSION</h3>
All non-board members with the exception of B. Morrison were dismissed from the room. 
Human Resources committee reported during the closed session.  J. Singh will
be the new committee member.
<h3>END CLOSED SESSION</h3>

<h3>6. Emerging Issues - Burton/Kaufman/Harvey</h3>
Committee reviewed its  report and was commended for the strong report and the many good
issues raised and identified.  Mansdorf requested they focus on a 5-year time frame.  This
committee will be involved in the August strategic planning meeting.

<h3>9. Strategic Plan - Rose</h3>
Rose reviewed the areas of the plan identified as needing expansion, attention, change, etc.
supplied by the board, staff, Committee Chairs, etc.  The Priority List included:
<ul><li>Programs and Services</li>
<li>1A Continuing Education</li>
<li>1C Lab Accreditation</li>
<li>1D Technical Support (Standards of Good Practice)</li>
<li>3B Leadership</li>
<li>- International Local Sections</li>
<li>- Identifying potential leaders</li>
<li>4A Fiscal Resources</li>
<li>5A Management awareness of need for industrial hygiene</li>
<li>7C Scope and Practice of IH</li>
<li>- Expand structure, programs and services to support redefinition by 1997</li>
<li>7D Unite the profession by 1998</li>
<li>AIHA technical committee structure - SIGs</li>
<li>Partnerships/Coalition Building</li></ul>

<h3>INFORMATION ITEMS</h3>
10, 11, 12, 13 - No reports were presented at this meeting.<br>
14, 15 - Consent Agenda - no reports were presented at this meeting<br>

<h3>16. Old Business - All</h3>
None

<h3>17. New Business - All</h3>
Lubs presented request of the Editorial Committee to change its name to Publications
Committee.
<p>
<b>MOTION:</b> Move to adopt name change from Editorial Committee to Publications
Committee. Passed.
<p>
<b>UTF update - </b>Any action taken on behalf of oneself (Board member, etc.) could be
viewed as acting for AIHA.  A joint ballot between AIHA and AAIH will go out not later than
July 1, 1996.  It will be mailed first class.  It will include a ballot and the UTF abstract.  AIHA
and AAIH will recommend a "yes" vote.  Academy will have responsibility for handling the
tabulating through an outside firm.  An open forum will be held at PCIH arranged through the
Academy.

<h3>Meeting was adjourned at 11:50 a.m.</h3>
<P>
<BR>
