<P>
 To help understand the grid, some
explanatory notes related to the asterisks, are: 
<P>
* Members: It is estimated that about 14,400 individuals are now paying full dues to one or more
of the associations.  This is based on estimates that about 90% of AAIH members are members
paying full dues in either the AIHA or the ACGIH, and that about 48% of ACGIH members are
also full dues-paying members of AIHA. Current member categories in ACGIH and AIHA are: 
<P>
<PRE>
Member category          ACGIH               AIHA<BR>
                    Dues      Members   Dues      Members<BR>
<BR>
Full member         $70       2,921     $100      8,759<BR>
Associate member    $70       221       $100      1,437<BR>
Affiliate member    $70       1,606     $100      653<BR>
Student member      $10       491       $10       243<BR>
Emeritus/Retired    0         278       0         615<BR>
Honorary            0         23        0         25<BR>
Technical member    $70       55                  none<BR>
Fellow                        none      $100      54<BR>
Organizational                none      $250/425  368<BR>
</PRE>
** Revenue, Expense, Excess: 1997 projected figures are used, to permit comparability with the
pro forma budget figures used later in this report. The figures for AIHA include the Foundation.
<P>
*** ABIH annually receives $70 from each Diplomate, of which $15 for each goes to AAIH.
<P>
**** Net Worth: Assets minus liabilities, based on 3/15/96 figures.

