<TITLE>Addendum B: UTF Criteria</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><CENTER>Addendum B: UTF Criteria</CENTER></H1>
<HR>
<H2>CHARACTERISTICS AGAINST WHICH UTF DECISIONS WILL BE EVALUATED</H2>

<OL>
<LI>Maintains and implements a concise mission statement that relates directly to all programs and
services.
<LI>Promotes and protects the profession of occupational and environmental health and the ethical
practice of the profession.
<LI>Establishes a flexible, effective governance structure that is responsive to changing
professional needs and emerging technical and political issues.
<LI>Establishes and regularly reviews committees and task forces according to the needs of the
organization.
<LI>Adheres to principles of strategic planning.
<LI>Identifies leaders and develops leadership among its members.
<LI>Enables and encourages peer and professional interaction, especially among industrial hygiene
special interest groups and regional chapters.
<LI>Develops credible technical information sources and workplace guidelines and assures
integrity of TLV/BEI process.
<LI>Sponsors technical conferences, symposia and workshops.
<LI>Publishes peer-reviewed scientific journal(s) with appropriate attention to the professional
needs of occupational, safety and health practitioners.
<LI>Provides quality continuing education programs.
<LI>Maintains the integrity of the certification (CIH) program, and seeks to implement
appropriate new certifications in occupational safety and health that evolve or are mandated.
<LI>Provides accreditation programs for occupational safety and health and related environmental
laboratories.
<LI>Provides accreditation programs for professional education at graduate and undergraduate
levels.
<LI>Influences state and national regulatory and legislative affairs.
<LI>Explores and develops international programs and services.
<LI>Promotes occupational safety and health research.
<LI>Attracts and retains competent and knowledgeable staff, including a strong chief staff officer.
<LI>Provides ancillary services for members.
<LI>Is responsive; non-bureaucratic; cost effective; fiscally strong; has a single membership
directory; and offers "one-stop" shopping.
</OL>
<P>
<BR>
