<A HREF="#notes">NOTES & ASSUMPTIONS</A><BR>
<HR>


<H2><A NAME="comparison">CONSOLIDATION DUES COMPARISON</A></H2>

Following is a comparison of dues in a consolidated organization operating at
an assumed margin of 6.7% with dues as they are today and as they would be
today if the existing organizations were also operating at a margin of 6.7%.

<PRE>
                        Status       Status Quo       Consolidated
Member Belongs To:        Quo     at a 6.7% Margin   at a 6.7% Margin

ACGIH + CIH              $140           $176                
AIHA + CIH                170            199             $160
Both + CIH                240            314
ACGIH                      70            106
AIHA                      100            129              110
Both                      170            235                
Neither + CIH              70             79               50
</PRE>


<H3>STATUS QUO, COOPERATIVE, FEDERATED & CONSOLIDATED MODELS DUES COMPARISON</H3>

Following is a comparison of dues rates in the various models considered by
the UTF.  Note that in the Status Quo, the four organizations taken together
operate at a margin of 4.1%.  In the Cooperative, Federated, and Consolidated
models, a margin of 6.7% is assumed since this was the "ideal" margin
indicated by members of the four Boards at the March 17, 1996 meeting. 
Therefore, in addition to the actual Status Quo at 4.1%, the Status Quo is
also shown at a margin of 6.7% for purposes of comparability.
<PRE>
                 Status Quo  Status Quo     
                   at 4.1%    at 6.7%   Coop      Fed       Consol

ACGIH + CIH         $140      $176      $176      $164 
AIHA + CIH           170       199       199       208      $160
Both + CIH           240       314       314       286
ACGIH                 70       106       106        78
AIHA                 100       129       129       122       110
Both                 170       235       235       200
Neither + CIH         70        79        79        86        50
</PRE>
<HR>

