<HEAD>
<TITLE>Addendum D: About the UTF</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><CENTER>Addendum D: About the UTF</CENTER></H1>
<HR>
<H2>MEMBERS OF THE UNIFICATION TASK FORCE </H2>

<STRONG>Lawrence R. Birkner</STRONG>, CIH, CSP, REA, Member, AIHA since 1976 and now a Fellow; served
AIHA as Director, Chair of the Respirator, Public Relations and Emerging Issues Committees;
President, Southern California Section, AIHA; authored first edition of AIHA's Respiratory
Protection Manual and Guideline and co-authored second edition; Past President, AAIH;
extensive program development and management experience in occupational hygiene, safety,
product safety and EH&S auditing; now Senior Health and Safety Consultant for ARCO; Vice
President /Technical Director for McIntyre, Birkner & Associates. 
<P>

<STRONG>Theodore A. Felton</STRONG>, MPH, CIH, CSP, Manager, Industrial Safety and Hygiene, General Electric
Company (Nuclear Energy); formerly with Lawrence Livermore Laboratory, University of
California; served as Past President of both AAIH and the Northern California Section of AIHA;
member of AIHA and a past national Board member; currently a Director, ABIH; registered as a
Professional Engineer (PE) in California.
<P>

<STRONG>Thomas G. Grumbles</STRONG>, CIH; currently Manager, Product Safety and Occupational Health for
CONDEA Vista Company, Houston, Texas; served as AAIH counselor; Chair of Joint Ethics
Committee; member of AIHA Ethics and Oversight Committee; President and Treasurer, Gulf
Coast Section, AIHA; currently a member of the Editorial Board of the ACGIH Journal; winner
of the 1990 AIHA Kusnetz Award.
<P>
<STRONG>Robert L. Harris</STRONG>, Ph.D., CIH, Professor Emeritus of Environmental Engineering at University of
North Carolina; served in the Public Health Service as Chief of Engineering in the pre-NIOSH
Division of Occupational Health, and as Director of the Bureau of Abatement and Control of the
pre-EPA National Air Pollution Control Administration; member of AAIH, ACGIH and AIHA,
and has served in the ABIH; an honorary member of AIHA and recipient of the AAIH Henry F.
Smyth, Jr., the ACGIH Meritorious Achievement  and the AIHA Cummings Memorial Awards.
<P>
<STRONG>Jake Jakubowski</STRONG>, CIH, employed by Pharmacia and Upjohn, Inc, in Kalamazoo, Michigan;
currently assigned to the Compliance Engineering Unit within the Company's bulk
pharmaceutical manufacturing division; has been with Pharmacia and Upjohn for three years;
prior to joining the Company, was a military industrial hygienist; retired from the United States
Army as a Lieutenant Colonel; currently serves as a Director for ABIH.
 <P>

<STRONG>Steven P. Levine</STRONG>, PH.D., CIH, Professor of Industrial Health, University of Michigan since 1982.
Served AIHA as Co-Founder/Vice-Chair, Hazardous Waste Committee, Co-Chair ISO/OHSMS 
and IH Research Priorities Task Forces, Member, Board of Directors; was member of Michigan
Industrial Hygiene Society Board; winner of AIHA John White and Drumbuster awards; co-author of AIHA monograph and Journal papers on OHS Management Systems, and of AIHA
OHS Management System itself;  Director of WHO Collaborating Center for Occupational
Health at U.M.
<P>

<STRONG>Henry J. Muranko</STRONG>, MPH, CIH, CSP, Founder and Principal, Muranko & Associates, Inc., a
consulting firm in occupational and environmental hygiene and safety, in Scottsdale, Arizona;
past Secretary/Treasurer, ABIH; former Senior Editor, AIHA Journal, and a past AIHA Director
and President; Fellow of the AIHA; affiliate member of ACGIH; trustee of the AIHA
Foundation; member of the AIHA International Affairs Committee.
<P>

<STRONG>Lee Smith</STRONG>, MS, CIH, a Captain in the United States Navy; member of ACGIH and AIHA for
over 16 years; wide range of occupational health and environmental experience in the DOD
Sector; a graduate of East Tennessee State University and Colorado State University; presently
Officer-in-Charge of Navy Environmental and Preventive medicine Unit No.5 in San Diego,
California.
<P>

<STRONG>David Utterback</STRONG>, Ph.D., CIH;  Industrial hygienist with the National Institute for Occupational
Safety and Health Division of Surveillance Hazard Evaluation and Field Studies since 1992; 
previously taught at California State University in Fresno and at the University of South
Carolina; member and then Chair of the Permanent Conference Committee as well as the AIHA
Analytical Chemistry Committee; member, ACGIH/AIHA joint task force for occupational
exposure databases; elected Vice-Chair Elect of ACGIH in 1996. 
<P>
<STRONG>Kenneth M. Wallingford</STRONG>, MS, CIH, Indoor Environmental Quality (IEQ) Research Coordinator
for NIOSH's Hazard Evaluations and Technical Assistance Branch; previously served in other
industrial hygiene management, research and technical positions at NIOSH and in private
consulting practice; graduate of the University of Cincinnati; member of AAIH, ACGIH and
AIHA; served as Chair of ABIH, Chair of AIHA's IEQ Committee, and a member of the 4-IH
Coordinating Committee. 
<P>

<STRONG>Thomas J. Walker</STRONG>, CIH (Ret), CSP (Ret), PE, graduate of the Athenaeum of Ohio; Masters
degrees in Education and in Environmental Health from Xavier University and the University of
Cincinnati; taught chemistry and biology in Cincinnati; worked for Dep't. of Health surveying
licenses users of X-ray equipment, as Manager of Industrial Hygiene for Kaiser Aluminum and
Chemical Corporation and had his own consulting practice, which was merged into FPE Group
in 1986; with his wife Lillian, now consults from Reno, Nevada. 
<P>

<STRONG>Joan A. Wronski</STRONG>, CIH, is Laboratory Director for AIHA accredited KRMS/NATLSCO
laboratory in Long Grove, Illinois; currently Secretary/Treasurer of AAIH; past Secretary of
AIHA; received her B.S. in Chemistry in 1964 and is certified in Chemical Aspects by the ABIH.


<H3>EX OFFICIO MEMBERS OF THE UNIFICATION TASK FORCE</H3>

<STRONG>Gordon Banks</STRONG>, CAE,  (Certified Association Executive) Executive Director of AIHA since
February, 1989; 30 years  experience as association executive with 4 associations; past president,
Gr. Washington Society of Association Executives; active in American Society of Association
Executives, a former Board member, and winner of the 1981 Key Award, their highest honor;
