<HEAD>
<TITLE> AIHA Professional Liability Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1> AIHA Professional Liability Program</H1>
<HR>
<H2>A Program to Protect You While You're Creating A Safe And Healthy Work Environment
</H2>
<UL><LI>Professional Liability With Pollution Coverage.
<LI>Limits Starting at $500,000.
<LI>Minimum Premiums From $1,750.</UL></LI>
<P>
<H2>AIHA and Sedgwick</H2>
Taking the lead to provide members with the Comprehensive Professional Liability protection
they need as IHs, and the service they deserve as members of AIHA.
<P>
<H2>As an Industrial Hygienist, Are You Protected?</H2>
Industrial Hygienists can and have been sued.  The effects of a successful suit could be
catastrophic to a private practice. Even if the suit is unsuccessful, the legal costs can be sizable.
<P>
The litigious nature of society invites suit to even the most cautious scientist.  The unfortunate
reality is that third party allegations of negligence and breach of contract create liability
potential, regardless of fault.  The ultimate claim cost extends far beyond financial terms,
impacting professional reputation and disrupting work.
<P>
<H2>AIHA Professional Liability Program</H2>
Sedgwick and AIHA are pleased to offer the AIHA Professional Liability Program.  This
important member services program is the culmination of 23 months of intensive investigation,
research, and negotiation with numerous insurance companies on behalf of the AIHA
membership.  
<P>
The result is the AIHA Professional Liability Program where members benefit from specific
contract enhancements not normally available in the standard marketplace.  The program is
underwritten by an A rated carrier, exclusively offered through Sedgwick of  Virginia, and
available only to members of AIHA.
<P>
<H2>Who is Sedgwick?</H2>
Sedgwick is a leading provider of insurance broking, and risk management services.  However,
Sedgwick does a great deal more than package insurance programs.  We research new, emerging
areas of liability, and develop targeted, cost-effective insurance programs to meet the challenging
needs of the industry.
<P>
Sedgwick's underwriting and loss control expertise (including many in-house CIHs) enables us
to evaluate the technical needs of the IH profession.  Additionally, our dedication to
administrative procedures provides our clients with the assurance that even the smallest details
are being properly handled.
<P>
<H2>AIHA's Professional Liability Program</H2>
Why do I need professional liability coverage? Practically any organization or individual who
improperly performs services can cause a client to suffer economic loss.  As an IH, you can be
held legally responsible for damages suffered by your client, as a result of your, or your
employees', failure to meet the level of performance, quality, fitness or durability warranted or
represented by you.<BR>
As an IH, why do I need pollution/asbestos coverage?  While you may not be involved in the
actual remediation of pollutants such as asbestos, your exposure to liability for these losses is
inherent.  
<P>
For example:<BR>
During  your services as an IH you failed to identify the existence of asbestos-containing
materials. You would need pollution coverage in order for the policy to respond.  Suppose in
your inspections for other potential pollutants you caused a release, exposing employees?  Again,
pollution coverage would be required.  Many IHs include in their services oversight of
reme-diation projects.  You could be held as a potentially responsible party, again requiring
pollution
coverage.
<P>
Who is insured by this program?  The AIHA Professional Liability Program Policy will cover the
named insured and any past or present employee, director, partner or executive officer while
acting within the scope of their duties on behalf of the named insured, or any person for whose
Wrongful Act the insured is legally responsible for.
<P>
<H2>What are the program features?</H2>
<B>LIMITS</B><BR>
<I>Five Different Limit Options Available:</I><BR>
$500,000 per claim - subject to - $500,000 annual aggregate <BR>
$500,000 per claim - subject to - $1,000,000 annual aggregate <BR>
$1,000,000 per claim - subject to - $1,000,000 annual aggregate <BR>
$1,000,000 per claim - subject to - $2,000,000 annual aggregate <BR>
$2,000,000 per claim - subject to - $2,000,000 annual aggregate <BR>
<I>(excess limits available on a per case basis)</I><BR>
<P>
<B>PREMIUM</B> Competitive group rate pricing <BR>
<B>DEDUCTIBLE</B> $2,500 standard deductible <BR>
<P>
<B>PREMIUM</B> Minimum premiums starting at $1,750<BR>
<B>DEDUCTIBLE</B> Credits for higher deductibles <BR>
<I>Rating based on annual revenues from IH work</I><BR>
<P>
<B>COVERAGE TERMS</B><BR>
<UL><LI>Claims made basis
<LI>Prior acts coverage available
<LI>Customized definition of "Professional Business Services" for IH profession
<LI>Duty to defend
<LI>Insurer "pays on behalf of" Insured vs. reimbursement
<LI>Pollution coverage, if caused by the performance of professional services, by or at the
direction of the insured.</UL></LI>
<P>
<H2>How do I apply for coverage?</H2>
<B>PHONE - </B>Contact the AIHA Program Administrator at Sedgwick of Virginia, Inc., toll
free at 800-448-9729, to answer any questions you may have.
<P>
<B>WEB PAGE - </B>Contact the AIHA Web Page for direct access to the program
information and application.  Application will link directly to the AIHA Program Administrator
at Sedgwick of Virginia via the internet for a no-obligation premium quotation.
<P>
<B>FAX ON DEMAND - </B>Contact AIHA's fax on demand service, (703) 641-INFO, enter
the Insurance program document number 1003, and program information will be faxed directly
to you.
<P>
<B>QUESTIONS - </B>Feel free to contact the AIHA Program Administrator at 800-448-9729.

<A HREF= "http://www.sedgwickna.com">Sedgwick James of Virginia, Inc.</A><BR>
7799 Leesburg Pike, North Tower, Suite 1000<BR>
Falls Church, Virginia 22043-2412<BR>

<P>
