<HEAD>
<TITLE>THE BULK ASBESTOS PROFICIENCY ANALYTICAL TESTING PROGRAM
(BAPAT)
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1>The Bulk Asbestos Proficiency Analytical Testing (BAPAT)
Program</H1>
<P>The Bulk Asbestos Proficiency Analytical Testing Program
serves as an external quality
assurance program for laboratories analyzing bulk building
materials by polarized light
microscopy (PLM).  It is designed to provide bulk audit samples
on a quarterly basis, and to
provide a means by which a laboratory can evaluate its ability to
characterize bulk materials. 
The program is strictly qualitative in nature.
</P>
<HR>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#BULK3"> What are the requirements for the
program?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#BULK4"> What do participants receive?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="fax.html"> Fees and application for the program</A> 
</UL>
<BR>
<H2><A NAME="BULK3">What are the requirements for the
program?</A></H2>
<P>The BAPAT Program is conducted by the Research Triangle
Institute, under the direction of
AIHA and its Industrial Hygiene Laboratory Accreditation
Committee.  Each round, laboratories
are required to classify samples of bulk building materials as
asbestos-containing or not, and to
identify the asbestos type(s) present in the samples.  In
addition, participants are asked to
provide semi-quantitative estimates of the amount of asbestos
present, and identification and
semi-quantitation of other fibrous and nonfibrous components of
the samples, where possible. 
However, evaluation of the laboratory's performance is based only
on sample classification and
asbestos identification.</P>
<P>Unlike the National Institute of Standards and Technology's
(NIST) National Voluntary
Laboratory Accreditation Program (NVLAP), this program offers no
certification or
accreditation.  For this reason, no on-site visits will be made
to your facility, and no specific
personnel, facility, or test method requirements will be
stipulated by AIHA.  This allows the
freedom for the laboratory to refine analytical techniques, train
new analysts, and improve the
performance of experienced analysts at no risk to the
laboratory's AIHA or NVLAP
credentials.</P>
<H2><A NAME="BULK4">What do participants receive?</A></H2>
<P>Participating laboratories will receive four samples in each
of four quarterly test rounds. 
These samples, the great majority of which are "real-world"
materials from abatement projects,
may contain any of the asbestos types in a variety of matrices
and binders typical of bulk
building and insulation materials.  Materials known to pose
difficulties to laboratories, such as
those containing low asbestos percentages or asbestos
"look-alike" fibers, as well as nonfriable
materials such as vinyl tile and cementitious or asphalyic
products, are frequently used.  These
samples remain the property of the laboratory and can serve both
as in-house quality control
samples and quantitation calibration reference samples. 
Laboratories are allowed one calendar
month in which to complete their analyses and submit their
results.</P>
<P>At the conclusion of each test round, each laboratory will
receive an extensive report of the
analysis that summarizes its results, provides the qualitative
and semi-quantitative reference
values for the samples, and includes a summary of the overall
performance of all laboratories
participating in the round.  Difficulties with the analysis of
specific samples in that round are
addressed, and suggestions for improving the laboratory's
qualitative and semi-quantitative
analyses are offered.  These reports are distributed one calendar
month after the results submittal
deadline so that the participant receives performance and
analysis feedback in as timely a manner
as possible.</P>
<BR>
<BR>
<P>For more information on the Bulk Asbestos Proficiency Testing
Program, contact Kim Bacon at (703) 849-8888; 
 <A HREF="mailto:kbacon.org">kbacon@aiha.org</A></P>
<BR>
<A HREF="accred.html">Back to Accreditation Page</A> | <A
HREF="index.html">Back to AIHA Home Page</A>
</BODY>
