<HTML>
<!--aat1.html-->
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Asbestos Analytical Testing Program (AAT)
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1>Asbestos Analyst Testing (AAT) Program</H1>
<P> The Asbestos Analysis Testing Program is designed for individual asbestos analysts
performing fiber-counting procedures on the job site.  Samples are provided on a quarterly basis
with the opportunity for the analyst to override his scores using retest samples.  Asbestos samples
are aerosol generated and distributed by SRI International, with data analysis performed by
AIHA. </P>
<HR>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#AAT3"> Who should participate in the AAT Program?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#AAT4">Who can participate in the AAT?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#AAT5">How does the AAT program work?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="fax.html">Fees and application for the program</A>
</UL>
<BR>
<H2><A NAME="AAT3">Who should participate in the AAT Program?</A></H2>
<P>Analysts who perform fiber-counting procedures at the job site need assurance of the quality
of their work, which can be provided by this program.  Analysts who desire to be listed in the
AAR must participate in the AAT.</P>
<H2><A NAME="AAT4">Who can participate in the AAT?</A></H2>
<P> The AAT Program is a performance testing program for asbestos analysts who desire to be
listed in the Asbestos Analysts Registry (AAR).  The AAT Program provide clients with
information on the quality of the sevices provided.</P>
<H2><A NAME="AAT5">How does the AAT program work?</A></H2>
<P> When an organization enrolls in the AAT Program, each analyst is assigned an ID number
and sample kits are sent out quarterly.  One sample kit can serve up to five analysts.  Sample
analysis must be performed using the latest version of the NIOSH 7400 method for counting
fibers.  Analytical procedures must be in compliance with the OSHA asbestos standard, CFR
1910.1001.</P>
<BR>
<BR>
<P>For more information on the AAT Program, contact Paul Z. Balcer at (703) 849-8888; <A
HREF="mailto:pbalcer@aiha.org">pbalcer@aiha.org</A></P>
