<BODY>
<H1>AIHA INTERNATIONAL ACCREDITED LABORATORIES</H1>
Updated January 16, 1997<BR>
<HR>
Click on the country to jump to that section...<BR>
<A HREF="#canada">Canada</A> | <A HREF="#hongkong">Hong Kong</A> | <A
HREF="#japan">Japan</A> | <A
HREF="#spain">Spain</A> | <A HREF="#taiwan">Taiwan</A>
<HR>
The letters in parentheses indicate analysis in which the laboratory participates.  For example,
(MXXO) indicates a laboratory participates in Metals and Organics. An "X" does not indicate an
analyte. Users should check with individual laboratories for current proficiency status if such
information is desired.<BR>
<UL>
<LI>M - Metals      
<LI>S -  Silica    
<LI>A - Asbestos and other fibers
<LI>O-  Organic Solvents   
<LI>X - Laboratory does not analyze that analyte class.</P>  
</UL>
<BR>
