<HEAD>
<TITLE>Biological Monitoring Laboratories and CLIA</TITLE>
</HEAD>
</BODY>
<H1>Biological Monitoring Laboratories and the Clinical Laboratory Improvement Act (CLIA)
of
1988</H1>
<P>Laboratories performing biological monitoring analyses fall under the jurisdiction of CLIA. 
A
CLIA Laboratory Certificate of Compliance must be obtained and laboratories must be licensed
in
their respective states.</P>
<P>With few exceptions, CLIA encompasses all testing, regardless of where it is performed, as
long as
it is performed on materials derived from the human body for the purpose of providing
information for
the diagnosis, prevention or treatment of any disease or impairment of, or the assessment of
health of,
human beings.</P>  
<P>For more information, contact Fred Grunder at (703) 849-8888 or email: <A
HREF="mailto:fgrunder@aiha.org">fgrunder@aiha.org</A>
<BR>
<BR>
