<HEAD>
<TITLE>S.Z. Mansdorf Press Release</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H2><CENTER>S. ZACK MANSDORF ASSUMES THE PRESIDENCY OF
AIHA</CENTER></H2>

<P>
     (WASHINGTON, June 3, 1996) -- S. Zack Mansdorf, Ph.D., CIH, CSP, QEP, assumed
the presidency of the American Industrial Hygiene Association (AIHA) last month in
Washington, D.C., at the American Industrial Hygiene Conference & Exposition (AIHCE) 1996.
<P>
     For the past year, Mansdorf has served as the president-elect of AIHA and will serve a
one-year tenure as president of the association.  His years of involvement with AIHA have
included lecturing or teaching continuing education courses.  He is currently employed as the
director of Liberty International Risk Services for Liberty International, a subsidiary of Liberty
Mutual Group, in Boston.
<P>
     Mansdorf has been an active member since 1977 and is a certified industrial hygienist
(CIH), a certified safety professional (CSP), and a qualified environmental professional (QEP).
<P>
     Mansdorf has 21 years of extensive knowledge in the occupational health and safety field. 
He has engineered health, safety, and environmental projects or studies for government, private
industry, and academic institutions.
<P>
      Mansdorf is the former director of environmental health services for Clayton
Environmental Consultants, Inc., the company to which he sold his firm, Mansdorf & Associates,
in Stow, Ohio.  He has also held industrial hygiene positions with the Occupational Safety and
Health Administration (OSHA), Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company, and the Midwest
Research Institute.
<P>
     Mansdorf is a graduate of the University of Akron and earned his Ph.D. from the
University of Kansas in the field of environmental engineering.  He holds masters' degrees in
industrial and environmental health and industrial safety from the University of Michigan and
Central Missouri State University, respectively.
<P>

<HR>
     The American Industrial Hygiene Association, with more than 12,000 members, is the world's
largest association representing occupational and environmental health and safety specialists.<P>

For More Information Contact:<P>

<A HREF="mailto:cfeheley@aiha.org">Christine Feheley</A><BR>
