<H2><CENTER>AIHA ANNOUNCES NEW BOARD OF DIRECTORS</CENTER></H2>

<P>
(Washington, June 10, 1996) -- The American Industrial Hygiene Association (AIHA) installed a
new board of directors last month in Washington, D.C., at the American Industrial Hygiene
Conference & Exposition (AIHCE) 1996.
<P> 
The board of directors is selected via a mail ballot by the membership.  AIHA's new board
members are as follows:
<P>
<UL>
<LI>S. Zack Mansdorf, Ph.D., CIH, CSP, QEP, assumes the presidency.  He is currently the
director of Liberty International Risk Services for Liberty International, a subsidiary of Liberty
Mutual Group, in Boston.  Mansdorf succeeds Vernon E. Rose, Dr PH, CIH, professor of public
health and director of the Deep South Center for Occupational Health and Safety at the
University of Alabama at Birmingham.
<P>
<LI>D. Jeff Burton, CIH, PE, CSP, president of IVE Incorporated, Bountiful, Utah, moves from
vice president to president-elect.
<P>
<LI>James C. Rock, Ph.D., CIH, PE, director of Texas Occupational Health & Safety Institute
and associate professor of the college of engineering for Texas A&M University, College
Station, Texas, takes over as vice president.
<P>
<LI>William L. Dyson, Ph.D., CIH, becomes the treasurer.  He is the president of Health and
Hygiene, Inc., in Greensboro, North Carolina.  Dyson succeeds Loren A. Anderson Jr., CIH,
manager of product safety for PPG Industries Coatings and Resins Group in Allison Park,
Pennsylvania.
<P>
<LI>Thomas G. Grumbles, CIH, is the new secretary-elect. Grumbles is manager of product
safety and occupational health for the Vista Chemical Company, Houston, Texas.
</UL>
<P>
In addition, the association membership selected three new directors to the board.  The new
directors are as follows:
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Donna M. Doganiero, CIH, U.S. Army Center for Health Promotion and Preventive
Medicine, Aberdeen Proving Ground, Maryland.
<P>
<LI>Peter L. Lubs, CIH, The Lubrizol Corporation, Wickliffe, Ohio.
<P>
<LI>Jaswant Singh, Ph.D., CIH, Clayton Environmental Consultants, Inc., Cypress, California.
<P>
<HR>
     The American Industrial Hygiene Association, with more than 12,000 members, is the world's
largest association representing occupational and environmental health and safety specialists.<P>

