<H2><CENTER>AMERICAN INDUSTRIAL HYGIENE ASSOCIATION (AIHA)
ANNOUNCES AGREEMENT WITH SEDGWICK JAMES OF VIRGINIA TO PROVIDE
PROFESSIONAL LIABILITY INSURANCE COVERAGE FOR ITS
MEMBERS</H2></CENTER>
<P>
(Washington, Dec. 2, 1996) -- The American Industrial Hygiene Association (AIHA) has
negotiated an arrangement with Sedgwick James of Virginia, a leading insurance broker and
provider of risk management services, for professional liability insurance exclusively for AIHA
members.  This additional membership benefit is being introduced in response to numerous focus
group discussions, member surveys and member phone calls.
<P>
AIHA and Sedgwick are leading the way in providing members with the comprehensive
professional liability protection they need and the service they deserve as AIHA members.  The
AIHA Professional Liability Program is designed to protect occupational and environmental
health and safety professionals from liability as they work to create a safe and healthy
environment.  This program, the result of much investigative research and negotiation, will
benefit members with specific contract enhancements not normally available in the standard
marketplace.  Sedgwick has a solid reputation for expertise in underwriting and loss control, for
researching new emerging areas of liability and for dedicated customer service.
<P>
Interested AIHA members should contact Sedgwick James of Virginia at (800) 448-9729 or
(703) 917-4000 for program details and rate quotations.
<P>
The American Industrial Hygiene Association, with more than 12,000 members, is
the world's largest association serving occupational and environmental health and safety
professionals.
