<Title> AIHA Offers Non-Confining Knowledge on Confined Space Entry</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BR>
<CENTER><H1>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>
PRESS RELEASE</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
Contact:<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:cfeheley@aiha.org"> Christine Feheley</A><BR>
<A HREF="mailto:vpatterson@aiha.org"> Valerie Patterson</A><BR>
(703) 849-8888 <BR>
(703) 207-3561 fax <BR>
<HR>
<H2><CENTER> AIHA OFFERS NON-CONFINING KNOWLEDGE ON CONFINED
SPACE ENTRY</H2></CENTER>
<P>
(Washington, December 27, 1996) -- A new AIHA Press publication, <I>Field Guidelines for
Temporary Ventilation of Confined Spaces with an Emphasis on Hotwork</I>, addresses an
important and sometimes overlooked aspect of confined space entry. Overhead slides that can be
used for training are included with this unique resource.
<P>
These field guidelines, particularly useful as an educational tool for employees with limited
ventilation training, provide examples of techniques for successful ventilation of confined spaces
where hotwork such as welding or thermal cutting produces fumes and gases requiring removal.
Other aspects of this useful resource include: ventilation techniques described in the guide
maximize effectiveness of confined space ventilation and provide for compliance with relevant
OSHA ventilation requirements for hotwork; designed to encourage use on the job site by project
supervisors and planners, IHs, safety professionals and others responsible for ventilating
confined spaces; and examples are oriented toward ventilation of vessels in petrochemical plants,
but are useful in virtually all facilities.
<P>
<I>Field Guidelines for Temporary Ventilation of Confined Spaces with an Emphasis on
Hotwork</I> is available for $48 to AIHA members and $60 to nonmembers. Call AIHA
Support Services at (703) 849-8888 to order or for a free AIHA Publications Catalog.
<P><P>
