<Title> AIHA Publishes One-of-a-Kind Management Book With an Occupational Health and
Safety Perspective</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BR>
<CENTER><H1>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>
PRESS RELEASE</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
Contact:<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:cfeheley@aiha.org"> Christine Feheley</A><BR>
<A HREF="mailto:vpatterson@aiha.org"> Valerie Patterson</A><BR>
(703) 849-8888 <BR>
(703) 207-3561 fax <BR>
<HR>
<H2><CENTER>AMERICAN INDUSTRIAL HYGIENE ASSOCIATION PUBLISHES ONE-OF-A-KIND MANAGEMENT BOOK WITH AN OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH AND SAFETY
PERSPECTIVE</H2></CENTER>
<P>
(Washington, December 20, 1996) -- <I>Management of People and Programs in Industrial
Hygiene</I> is a new publication from the AIHA Press, the AIHA publications program, that
directly links management techniques with the practice of occupational and environmental health
and safety, making it an invaluable resource to all in the field.  
<P>
Written by two authorities on management in the industrial hygiene capacity, this ground-breaking resource covers a variety of management principles and applies them to the practice of
industrial hygiene. Issuess addressed include: the industrial hygienist as leader and manager;
getting things done with people; building teams and programs; assembling industrial hygiene
program elements with clear-cut objectives; quality parameters for industrial hygiene practice;
measuring the success of an industrial hygiene program; total quality management in industrial
hygiene; fitting industrial hygiene into the company culture; and much more.
<P>
<I>Management of People and Programs in Industrial Hygiene</I> is $40 for AIHA members,
$50 for nonmembers, and can be ordered by calling AIHA at (703) 849-8888 or via fax at (703)
207-3561. For a list of other management-related AIHA Press publications, ask for a free copy of
the AIHA Publications Catalog.

