<HEAD>
<TITLE>PUBLIC RELATIONS & MARKETING HIGHLIGHTS</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1>Public Relations & Marketing Highlights<BR>
September/October 1996</H1>
<BR>
<P>
<H2>NEWS RELEASES</H2>
<UL><LI>"AIHA's <I>Field Guide for the Determination of Biological Contaminants in
Environmental Samples</I> Now Available" was mailed to trade press and committee chairs.
<LI>"American Industrial Hygiene Association Co-Sponsors First Traveling Museum Exhibit
Highlighting the Profession" was mailed to trade press and AIHA board members.</UL></LI>
<P>
<H2>PRESS REQUESTS AND INFORMATION</H2>
<UL><LI><I>A Safety & Health</I> reporter sought information regarding how safety directors
empower workers to identify and correct health hazards.
<LI>A writer from <I>Quality Progress</I> magazine requested information on AIHA's
publication <I>Occupational Health and Safety Management System: An AIHA Guidance
Document.</I>
<LI>A reporter with Gannett Suburban Newspapers asked for information to write an article
explaining how downsizing has affected worker safety and health.  Specific concerns targeted
were companies economizing on safety measures, not updating equipment and generally
scrimping on health safety efforts, thus potentially leading to repetitive stress injuries and other
worker injuries.
<LI>A reporter from Chelsea Group Ltd. asked about any recent IAQ news.
<LI>An article in <I>Safety Now</I> newsletter, "How Much Do You Know About Industrial
Hygiene?" included AIHA's definition of the various roles of industrial hygienists.  The article
also highlighted AIHA's "IH Issues in a Nutshell."
<LI><I>Occupational Health & Safety</I> announced the availability of AIHA's new
publication <I>Occupational Health and Safety Management System: An AIHA Guidance
Document.</I>
<LI>An <I>Occupational Health & Safety</I> article noted how to receive the most recent
edition of the AIHA Journal Consultants Listing.
<LI><I>Occupational Health and Safety</I> and<I> North Hills News Record</I> printed items
announcing Mine Safety Appliances Co.'s $50,000 contribution to the American Industrial
Hygiene Association Foundation, which awards nationwide scholarships to graduate students.
<LI>The <I>Journal of Protective Coatings and Linings</I> featured an item on the Lead Tech
'96 Conference naming AIHA as one of the co-sponsors.
<LI><I>Occupational Hazards</I> ran an article on correct calibration of air monitoring
instruments and featured some of Mary DeVany's "expert tips" on proper equipment calibration. 
DeVany is chair of AIHA's Confined Spaces Committee.
<LI><I>Industrial Fire World</I> listed AIHA's course "The Fundamentals of Industrial
Hygiene" that was held in San Antonio on Sept. 30 Oct. 4.

<LI><I>Journal of the Air & Waste Management Association</I> published the technical paper
titled "Review of Quantitative Standards and Guidelines for Fungi in Indoor Air."  The article
highlighted AIHA's many publications concerning indoor air quality.
<LI>The article "Laws, Company Safety Programs Make  Cancer Clusters' a Rarity," written by
a Daily Herald business writer, ran in the following 24 newspapers: <I>Algonquin/Lake In The
Hills Daily Herald; Arlington Heights Daily Herald; Barrington Daily Herald; Buffalo Grove
Daily Herald; Carol Stream Daily Herald; Des Plaines Daily Herald; Elgin Daily Herald; Elk
Grove Daily Herald; Glen Ellyn Daily Herald; Hanover Park Daily Herald; Hoffman
Estates Schaumburg Daily Herald; Itasca/Wood Dale Daily Herald; Kane County Daily Herald;
Lake Zurich/Waconda Daily Herald; Libertyville/Mundelein/Vernon Hills Daily Herald;
Lombard Daily Herald; Mount Prospect/Prospect Heights Daily Herald; Naperville/Lisle Daily
Herald; Palatine Daily Herald; Rolling Meadows Daily Herald; Roselle/Medinah Daily Herald;
West Chicago/Winfield Daily Herald; Wheaton Daily Herald; and Wheeling Daily Herald.</I> 
The article quoted Paul Hewitt, chairman of AIHA's Occupational Epidemiology Committee,
and Mike McNamara, chairman of AIHA's Workplace Environmental Exposure Level
Committee.  The AIHA chairmen talked about companies' safety and health programs and
protective guidelines.
<LI><I>Health Facilities Management</I> listed <I>Occupational Health and Safety
Management System: An AIHA Guidance Document</I> as a good resource to help
organizations implement occupational health and safety management systems.
<LI><I>Canadian Chemical News</I> published the AIHA course listing for "Fundamentals of
Industrial Hygiene."
<LI><I>CIM Bulletin</I> announced AIHA course listings "The Fundamentals of Industrial
Hygiene" and "Quantitative Industrial Hygiene."
<LI><I>Compliance Magazine</I> reported that AIHA installed its new board of directors at
AICHE in May.
<LI><I>Occupational Health & Safety</I> printed an article, "Harmonizing the Industrial
Hygiene Associations: How We Plan to Work Together," outlining the consolidation project.
<LI><I>Environmental Solutions</I> announced AIHA's Consultants Symposium: The
Business of Consulting, in their Conference Calendar.
<LI><I>Material Handling Engineering</I> published an article "Who's in Charge of
Ergonomics?" reviewing the pre-AIHCE Ergonomics Symposium.
<LI>The editor of <I>Material Handling Engineering</I> summarized Gregg LaBar's (senior
editor <I>Occupational Hazards</I>) recap of AIHCE in May and asked questions about
ergonomics and other issues.
<LI><I>The Hartford Courant</I> recorded AIHA's Connecticut River Valley Local Section
meeting in its calendar of events.
<LI><I>Safety and Health Today</I> printed the article "ACGIH Voices IH Unification
Worries" in its October issue.
<LI><I>Safety and Health Today</I> published an interview with AIHA President Zack
Mansdorf.
<LI><I>The Toledo Blade</I> announced an AIHA-sponsored tour of the Toledo water
treatment plant in its Coming Up section of the paper.
<LI><I>Indoor Environment Review</I> listed the Lead Tech '96 Conference in its calendar of
events and recognized AIHA as a co-sponsor.
<LI><I>Occupational Health & Safety</I> published an article on respirator program training
which suggested that it is desirable for instructors to have served either on ANSI's Respirator
Standards Committees or AIHA's Respiratory Protection Committee.
<LI><I>Indoor Environment Review</I> published an article entitled "Promoting An IAQ
Forum," mentioning AIHA as one of the larger associations sharing responsibility for IAQ.
<LI>Two reporters from <I>Quality Digest</I> wrote an article featuring quotes from Zack
Mansdorf, president, AIHA and Steven Levine, former co-chair of AIHA's Task Force for OHS
Management Systems.</UL></LI>
<P>
<H2>PR/MARKETING ACTIVITIES</H2>
<UL><LI>Received more than 274 requests for AIHA consumer brochures.
<LI>Sent IAQ brochures <I>Do I Work in a Sick Building?</I> and <I>Is Indoor Air Quality a
Problem in My Home?</I> to Daniel Levine, editor of <I>Disgruntled.</I>
<LI>Sent press kits to <I>The Washington Post</I> and <I>Fox Morning News</I> WTTG-TV
Channel 5 in response to a news item on Channel 5, which aired Oct. 1, regarding potential
dangers associated with lead paint on playground equipment.
<LI>Faxed Mark Katchen (AIHA member, Los Angeles Local Section) copy of <I>The
Synergist</I> article "Community Outreach Project Focuses on Occupational Health," which
outlined the combined AIHA/American Lung Association project.</UL></LI>
<P>
<H2>SPECIAL PUBLIC RELATIONS ACTIVITIES</H2>
<UL><LI>AIHA participated in the Northern Virginia Association of Realtors' Trade Show. 
AIHA distributed Operation Outreach brochures <I>Is Lead a Problem in My Home?</I> and
<I>Is Air Quality a Problem in My Home?</I> (in English and Spanish).  AIHA also circulated a
copy of the ad that discusses how AIHA can be beneficial in helping organizations comply with
lead paint disclosure procedures according to EPA and HUD's published final rule ER 9064-9088.
<LI>AIHA was represented at the Lead Tech '96 Conference in Washington,  D.C. (Oct. 7 9).
<LI>AIHA staff manned the association's booth and attended the Professional Conference of
Industrial Hygienists in Nashville, Tenn. (Oct. 14 17).
<LI>AIHA personnel staffed the booth and participated in the National Safety Council Congress
and Exposition in Orlando, Fla. (Oct. 28 30).</UL></LI>
